1
00:00:00,790 --> 00:00:09,200
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 6</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:02:07,419 --> 00:02:08,499
Was...

3
00:02:09,713 --> 00:02:10,803
Go Cheong-myeong

4
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,721
there to meet her?

5
00:02:16,762 --> 00:02:18,852
Chan-sung, come here!

6
00:02:22,768 --> 00:02:23,978
This came for you.

7
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:25,022
HOTEL DEL LUNA

8
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:26,652
It's from Man-wol.

9
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:28,110
-It's from Jang Man-wol?
-Yes.

10
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,530
THANK YOU

11
00:02:36,198 --> 00:02:37,408
"Thank you"?

12
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:39,785
<i>Don't run away.</i>

13
00:02:40,619 --> 00:02:43,659
Even if I go berserk, do crazy things,

14
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,825
and vanish one day,

15
00:02:47,918 --> 00:02:49,668
please stay by my side.

16
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:55,223
<i>I won't let you vanish.</i>

17
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:58,098
<i>Trust me.</i>

18
00:03:00,097 --> 00:03:01,767
She fired a competent guy like you,

19
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,888
but she eventually
ended up reinstating you.

20
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,765
I guess she wants to be nice to you now.

21
00:03:06,228 --> 00:03:07,728
My sincerity touched her heart.

22
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:21,082
My god, what's this?
Is this a tiger print suit?

23
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,617
<i>Make sure you get a good price for this.</i>

24
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:28,964
Then as a reward,
I'll get you a tiger print suit like this.

25
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:31,416
God, she's unbelievable.

26
00:03:31,837 --> 00:03:34,877
This is a luxury brand. It's really sexy.

27
00:03:34,965 --> 00:03:36,835
You should try it on. It'll look funny.

28
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:39,335
No, forget it.
Who wears tiger print suits?

29
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:42,679
But if you don't wear it,
Man-wol will feel upset.

30
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:44,524
It looks really expensive.

31
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:46,769
And it'll upset me as well.

32
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:48,482
I want to see how it looks on you.

33
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:55,111
I didn't give her the money I got
from selling the painting.

34
00:03:55,694 --> 00:03:57,404
Where did she get the money to buy this?

35
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:02,080
She wouldn't go to a luxury brand store
just to get a suit for me.

36
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:04,829
Hey, this is actually really nice.

37
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:07,661
Veronica's coming to Korea next week.
How about I buy the same suit?

38
00:04:07,748 --> 00:04:10,668
It might make me look
really wild and different.

39
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:12,841
No, don't do that.
You don't want to shock her.

40
00:04:13,545 --> 00:04:16,915
You know nothing
about being in a relationship.

41
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:19,757
It's necessary to surprise
your partner once in a while.

42
00:04:19,843 --> 00:04:20,723
Whatever.

43
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:23,472
Man-wol said she was going
to a department store the other day.

44
00:04:23,555 --> 00:04:25,015
I guess that's when she got this.

45
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:27,641
You met Jang Man-wol?

46
00:04:27,726 --> 00:04:28,886
Yes, a few days ago.

47
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:32,694
She asked me to help her sell something
she inherited from her grandfather.

48
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,611
What? "Something she inherited
from her grandfather"?

49
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:42,624
They're a couple of pure Arabian horses
on a farm in Qatar.

50
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:45,369
I heard even the royal family
wants to have those horses.

51
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:47,122
Do you think you can help me sell them?

52
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:51,496
Sanchez, are you close to Mansour
by any chance?

53
00:04:51,583 --> 00:04:52,633
Mansour?

54
00:04:53,335 --> 00:04:56,505
No, I'm not.
But purebred horses are very rare.

55
00:04:56,588 --> 00:04:59,338
So someone in my equestrian club
will want to buy them.

56
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,133
That's great news.

57
00:05:01,218 --> 00:05:04,048
If you help me sell those horses
at a high price,

58
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:08,727
I'll get you a white suit
just like this one.

59
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,729
But why are you asking me for help
instead of Chan-sung?

60
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:13,733
I can't trust him.

61
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:14,824
Why not?

62
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:19,493
He just got reinstated,
so he's really busy.

63
00:05:20,195 --> 00:05:21,815
Please help me with this, Sanchez.

64
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:26,077
If you ever happen to come
to my hotel in the future,

65
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,539
I promise that I'll treat you well.

66
00:05:28,537 --> 00:05:30,287
Oh, really?

67
00:05:30,539 --> 00:05:31,959
Of course.

68
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:33,829
My gosh.

69
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:40,047
The chairman...

70
00:05:46,137 --> 00:05:48,177
I sold the horses for your sake.

71
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:50,845
By the way,
those horses are really expensive.

72
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:53,847
She got those horses in return
for letting him make the dream call.

73
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:55,564
I should never be off my guard.

74
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:58,439
I should always make sure
to tighten the reins.

75
00:06:09,828 --> 00:06:13,158
Mr. Koo. All the guests are
requesting the special service.

76
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:16,419
They heard of this
because of Chairman Wang,

77
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:19,341
so many of them wish to make
a dream call to the living people.

78
00:06:19,546 --> 00:06:21,166
This is a service

79
00:06:21,256 --> 00:06:23,296
that Ms. Jang has only offered in secret

80
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:26,553
to guests who pay special fees.
What should we do?

81
00:06:27,262 --> 00:06:28,972
We should be fair
in providing our service.

82
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,095
I'll handle this.

83
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,700
Okay.

84
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,200
Hey.

85
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:57,880
What? Why didn't you put it on?

86
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:00,709
I was looking forward to seeing you
dressed in tiger print.

87
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:02,165
This is my workplace.

88
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,875
If the owner says it's fine,
then it's fine.

89
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:08,971
See? I even bought this
to wear when you come dressed

90
00:07:09,304 --> 00:07:10,724
like a tiger.

91
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:13,850
That's a horse print. A zebra.

92
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:16,352
What do you think? Pretty, isn't it?

93
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:17,726
It gets on my nerves.

94
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:19,478
You don't like it?

95
00:07:20,482 --> 00:07:21,782
You're so picky.

96
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:25,449
Fine, if you don't like
tiger prints or zebra prints,

97
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:28,525
then let's go. I'll get you
something that's your cup of tea.

98
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:29,815
We have no time to do that.

99
00:07:31,868 --> 00:07:34,368
We have a lot of special requests
from our guests.

100
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:35,707
You need to take care of them.

101
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:45,224
A dream call is only offered to those
who pay a special price.

102
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,298
You already got paid.

103
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,179
The horses. You took the horses.

104
00:07:50,261 --> 00:07:51,811
Darn you, Sanchez.

105
00:07:52,931 --> 00:07:54,721
I won't meddle with that money,

106
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:57,098
but you have to help the other guests.

107
00:07:57,185 --> 00:07:58,395
REQUEST FOR SPECIAL SERVICE

108
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:01,314
Chan-sung, do you think

109
00:08:01,398 --> 00:08:03,978
the dead will only say nice things
when they appear in a dream?

110
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:06,364
"I died because of you.
You have to die with me."

111
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:09,114
What if they resent and curse the living?

112
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:15,701
Resentment and cursing.

113
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:19,000
That's why I look into each and every one
of their cases

114
00:08:19,082 --> 00:08:22,172
and take a special price
only when the circumstances look right.

115
00:08:22,252 --> 00:08:23,752
It's not just about money!

116
00:08:27,132 --> 00:08:28,132
You're right.

117
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:30,141
I had the wrong idea about you.

118
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:32,013
It wasn't because of money.

119
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,559
You were concerned.

120
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:37,926
Yes. It's all for my guests' sake.

121
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:40,598
I only do it for those
who can pull this off.

122
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:42,267
What do you take me for?

123
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:45,109
In that case,

124
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,741
I will make some rules
to single out those who can do this.

125
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:55,288
Seriously!

126
00:08:56,286 --> 00:08:59,996
I'm the one who took the horses.
Why is he acting like that?

127
00:09:03,376 --> 00:09:05,836
I'll tell you the secret
to our <i>naengmyeon</i> stock.

128
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:08,880
It's because you were
the most diligent one among my staff.

129
00:09:09,424 --> 00:09:10,764
Listen up.

130
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:13,852
<i>Naengmyeon</i>?

131
00:09:14,179 --> 00:09:15,639
I love <i>naengmyeon</i> too.

132
00:09:15,722 --> 00:09:16,932
The secret is...

133
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:23,811
My gosh.

134
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:27,324
Is that you?

135
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:30,356
Thank you so much for everything.

136
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:33,985
Your band's music gave me
much comfort to my last breath.

137
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:36,655
-"Your band"?
-He must be in a band.

138
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:39,081
I knew your music and dance

139
00:09:39,162 --> 00:09:42,002
would end up touching
the heart of the world.

140
00:09:42,082 --> 00:09:43,882
That's not for someone she actually knew.

141
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:44,788
Look, it says...

142
00:09:44,876 --> 00:09:46,206
I WISH TO TELL SOMEONE I LOVE...

143
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:47,924
I love you!

144
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:49,804
I'll love you forever!

145
00:10:07,308 --> 00:10:08,428
Having fun?

146
00:10:08,601 --> 00:10:11,061
Stay on top of everything, will you?

147
00:10:12,313 --> 00:10:13,363
Yes.

148
00:10:21,739 --> 00:10:23,119
He's leaving today,

149
00:10:23,198 --> 00:10:25,488
and he wishes to talk to his wife
before he leaves.

150
00:10:25,909 --> 00:10:28,749
Am I allowed to make only one call?

151
00:10:28,912 --> 00:10:30,582
Yes, just one call.

152
00:10:31,957 --> 00:10:35,037
In that case, I wish to call someone else.

153
00:10:37,796 --> 00:10:40,046
I got into a car accident with my son.

154
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:47,890
I wish to talk to the man
who hit us with the truck.

155
00:10:48,223 --> 00:10:51,103
You cannot make a call
to blame or curse someone.

156
00:10:51,352 --> 00:10:52,312
Please leave.

157
00:10:52,394 --> 00:10:54,484
It's not that I wish
to blame or curse him.

158
00:10:56,774 --> 00:10:58,284
I wish to apologize to him.

159
00:11:06,325 --> 00:11:09,325
I'm glad you were just put on probation.

160
00:11:09,411 --> 00:11:12,831
Glad? Two people were
hit by my truck and died.

161
00:11:17,628 --> 00:11:19,458
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

162
00:11:21,256 --> 00:11:24,176
I can't do this job anymore.

163
00:11:24,259 --> 00:11:26,969
If you quit this job,
how will you make a living?

164
00:11:43,404 --> 00:11:46,204
You are the people I killed...

165
00:11:50,452 --> 00:11:51,752
I'm sorry.

166
00:11:52,746 --> 00:11:54,116
I'm so sorry.

167
00:11:54,706 --> 00:11:57,036
I can't be forgiven for what I have done.

168
00:11:58,335 --> 00:12:01,795
We're sorry.

169
00:12:03,841 --> 00:12:07,931
It's our fault for suddenly jumping
in front of your truck.

170
00:12:09,221 --> 00:12:10,511
It was a mistake.

171
00:12:11,974 --> 00:12:13,644
We had bad luck,

172
00:12:13,976 --> 00:12:16,436
but we gave you too much pain.

173
00:12:16,895 --> 00:12:17,935
I'm sorry.

174
00:12:25,696 --> 00:12:27,156
I hope

175
00:12:27,489 --> 00:12:30,199
your life doesn't get ruined
because of us.

176
00:12:31,076 --> 00:12:32,286
I'm sorry.

177
00:12:33,829 --> 00:12:35,159
And thank you.

178
00:12:50,596 --> 00:12:52,676
I feel much better now.

179
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,060
Son, shall we go?

180
00:12:58,395 --> 00:12:59,515
Thank you.

181
00:13:16,955 --> 00:13:18,575
Should we call it a day?

182
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:24,300
We only have a few guests left.
Let's finish up today.

183
00:13:24,630 --> 00:13:25,630
Tell them to come in.

184
00:13:35,224 --> 00:13:37,814
The flowers are in full bloom.

185
00:13:38,977 --> 00:13:40,897
Let's not be too worried.

186
00:13:41,063 --> 00:13:43,023
The flowers have finally bloomed.

187
00:13:43,106 --> 00:13:46,146
They might stay pretty like this
for a long time.

188
00:13:46,401 --> 00:13:49,491
Mago is trying to take Ms. Jang.

189
00:13:49,821 --> 00:13:53,331
Flowers bloom only to fall.

190
00:13:53,408 --> 00:13:57,198
We have to go before Ms. Jang does,

191
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,080
so let's prepare ourselves for that day.

192
00:14:14,972 --> 00:14:17,272
Gosh, I'm so tired.

193
00:14:18,559 --> 00:14:22,769
Do you know how tiring it is
to let ghosts talk to the living?

194
00:14:25,857 --> 00:14:29,857
But thanks to you, many people will smile
when they wake up from their dreams today.

195
00:14:30,946 --> 00:14:33,236
You've done well,
so I'll make you smile too.

196
00:14:34,449 --> 00:14:35,449
What?

197
00:14:35,993 --> 00:14:36,913
How?

198
00:14:36,994 --> 00:14:39,254
Are you going to put on
the tiger print suit?

199
00:14:39,329 --> 00:14:42,669
I knew it. You sent that to me
to make me look ridiculous.

200
00:14:42,833 --> 00:14:46,003
Hey, if I put in that much money
to have a good laugh,

201
00:14:46,086 --> 00:14:47,416
it means I tried very hard.

202
00:14:47,504 --> 00:14:50,264
I tried very hard to make you laugh too.

203
00:14:50,674 --> 00:14:52,974
I made a reservation
at the rice cake soup place

204
00:14:53,051 --> 00:14:56,351
where you failed to eat
and came back angry many times.

205
00:14:56,972 --> 00:14:58,022
Let's go.

206
00:14:58,348 --> 00:14:59,348
What?

207
00:14:59,808 --> 00:15:02,638
They don't take reservations. It takes
at least two hours to get a table.

208
00:15:02,728 --> 00:15:05,188
I used my connection from Harvard.

209
00:15:05,272 --> 00:15:06,902
Can you major in rice cake soup
at Harvard?

210
00:15:06,982 --> 00:15:08,652
The son of that restaurant is an alumnus.

211
00:15:11,194 --> 00:15:13,784
I reserved the entire place
at the closing time.

212
00:15:15,449 --> 00:15:16,579
Let us hurry.

213
00:15:18,243 --> 00:15:19,333
Hey, wait.

214
00:15:20,495 --> 00:15:22,575
You should change into an outfit
that fits the soup.

215
00:15:22,664 --> 00:15:26,254
This isn't an ordinary rice cake soup.
It's made with bead-shaped cakes.

216
00:15:26,835 --> 00:15:28,455
I'll wear something special.

217
00:16:08,001 --> 00:16:08,921
Look here.

218
00:16:09,002 --> 00:16:10,422
I'm okay.

219
00:16:13,882 --> 00:16:15,722
Sanchez is only three years older than me.

220
00:16:16,134 --> 00:16:18,144
If I eat three bowls
of rice cake soup today,

221
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:20,390
can I talk casually to you
like Sanchez does?

222
00:16:20,973 --> 00:16:21,893
What?

223
00:16:22,516 --> 00:16:24,936
Sanchez calls you by your first name.

224
00:16:26,561 --> 00:16:28,311
You want to be on a first name basis
with me?

225
00:16:32,442 --> 00:16:36,242
Okay, just eat 1,300 bowls
of rice cake soup.

226
00:16:37,114 --> 00:16:38,824
Even Kim Jun-hyun can't eat that much.

227
00:16:38,907 --> 00:16:40,617
Don't underestimate Kim Jun-hyun.

228
00:16:41,868 --> 00:16:42,828
Okay, then.

229
00:16:42,911 --> 00:16:45,621
One rice cake will be worth one year.

230
00:16:45,914 --> 00:16:47,874
No, one rice cake for one hundred years.

231
00:16:48,917 --> 00:16:52,207
You fraud from Harvard!
You think you could age that easily?

232
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:54,840
After I eat 13 rice cakes,

233
00:16:54,923 --> 00:16:56,843
I'll start calling you Man-wol.

234
00:16:58,677 --> 00:16:59,887
Do as you please.

235
00:16:59,970 --> 00:17:03,220
When a human ages 1,300 years, he dies.

236
00:17:03,807 --> 00:17:06,437
Challenge. I'll take 200 years first.

237
00:17:09,062 --> 00:17:10,862
It tastes better
because it's worth 200 years.

238
00:17:10,981 --> 00:17:14,031
Being on a roll, I add 300 years more.

239
00:17:20,824 --> 00:17:22,164
They look so pretty now.

240
00:17:22,993 --> 00:17:24,543
Why must they fall?

241
00:17:26,663 --> 00:17:27,833
It's sad.

242
00:18:03,533 --> 00:18:06,243
Now I have 300 years left.

243
00:18:06,703 --> 00:18:07,833
Are you nervous?

244
00:18:07,913 --> 00:18:09,963
Then, I just have to eat 500 years more.

245
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:11,040
Are you stupid?

246
00:18:11,291 --> 00:18:12,581
I will eat faster.

247
00:18:12,667 --> 00:18:14,337
No, I will eat faster.

248
00:18:14,419 --> 00:18:16,049
I now have 100 years left.

249
00:18:16,296 --> 00:18:17,666
Add 200 years for me.

250
00:18:17,756 --> 00:18:19,666
I was famous for eating fast at Harvard.

251
00:18:19,758 --> 00:18:21,258
I'm already 3,500 years old.

252
00:18:21,343 --> 00:18:23,513
-Adding 600 years.
-I'm 3,600 years old now.

253
00:18:23,595 --> 00:18:25,555
You can't beat me. Just acknowledge it.

254
00:18:25,639 --> 00:18:27,179
I'll also eat those earrings after this.

255
00:18:27,265 --> 00:18:28,225
Nonsense.

256
00:19:10,934 --> 00:19:12,524
I've found the motive for the murders.

257
00:19:13,270 --> 00:19:14,770
It's this website called <i>Helllo</i>.

258
00:19:14,938 --> 00:19:16,768
<i>Helllo</i>? Is it some social club?

259
00:19:16,857 --> 00:19:20,607
It's "Hell" and <i>"lo,"</i> meaning "to Hell."

260
00:19:20,735 --> 00:19:23,315
The name is a play on words.

261
00:19:23,488 --> 00:19:25,658
<i>Helllo</i>. What is the website for?

262
00:19:25,740 --> 00:19:28,740
It's an old community
with more than 100 thousand members.

263
00:19:28,827 --> 00:19:31,117
At first, they just shared
their problems on it.

264
00:19:31,204 --> 00:19:34,374
But it's gradually become a real hell.

265
00:19:34,457 --> 00:19:37,667
Now, they post curses and slanders
about other people.

266
00:19:37,752 --> 00:19:40,592
It's like an emotional trash can.

267
00:19:40,755 --> 00:19:42,875
-So?
-The suspect posted

268
00:19:42,966 --> 00:19:44,716
several slanders about his wife.

269
00:19:44,801 --> 00:19:48,641
He wrote comments on slanders
about six others who were killed.

270
00:19:48,722 --> 00:19:50,562
The slanders about the victims

271
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:52,980
had a high number of views and comments.

272
00:19:54,895 --> 00:19:58,185
Now you're looking
at the post and comments

273
00:19:58,273 --> 00:19:59,693
criticizing one of the victims.

274
00:19:59,774 --> 00:20:01,484
KILL, KILL!

275
00:20:01,568 --> 00:20:03,858
If one uploads a slandering post
about people he hates,

276
00:20:04,321 --> 00:20:07,201
the others curse them together.
That's what they do on the website.

277
00:20:07,282 --> 00:20:10,202
What about the suspect?
Did he carry out the curse?

278
00:20:11,536 --> 00:20:12,906
He thinks he's some kind of demon?

279
00:20:12,996 --> 00:20:15,576
Except for Lee Do-yeon,
the wife of the suspect,

280
00:20:15,665 --> 00:20:18,745
the victims were killed by someone
who they had never met.

281
00:20:19,377 --> 00:20:20,797
They didn't even know why.

282
00:20:22,881 --> 00:20:25,971
So this man is not the killer, right?

283
00:20:28,178 --> 00:20:30,058
I told you. I was right.

284
00:20:30,138 --> 00:20:32,138
The owner of that car is the killer.

285
00:20:32,390 --> 00:20:34,730
There was a ghost in that car too.
You saw it.

286
00:20:34,851 --> 00:20:37,941
But you can't call the police
without any evidence.

287
00:20:40,398 --> 00:20:41,568
There's the composite sketch.

288
00:20:41,816 --> 00:20:44,436
That thing you always see
in criminal investigation dramas.

289
00:20:44,694 --> 00:20:45,704
Let's do that.

290
00:20:45,904 --> 00:20:48,324
I'm good at drawing.

291
00:20:50,951 --> 00:20:54,911
You'll get into trouble
if Ms. Jang finds out about this.

292
00:20:55,288 --> 00:20:58,628
Tell me everything you remember about him.

293
00:20:58,708 --> 00:20:59,708
Tell me anything.

294
00:21:01,044 --> 00:21:04,634
81GI 0963

295
00:21:14,849 --> 00:21:17,309
I didn't meet the Koo Chan-sung guy.

296
00:21:17,394 --> 00:21:18,944
I moved the stuff with a high school girl.

297
00:21:19,020 --> 00:21:22,650
I really had a hard time
because my car broke down.

298
00:21:23,358 --> 00:21:25,938
Do you know the girl's name
or her phone number?

299
00:21:26,027 --> 00:21:27,607
I don't know her phone number.

300
00:21:27,696 --> 00:21:30,196
She contacted us through the SNS account.

301
00:21:31,616 --> 00:21:33,696
Do you really work
at an entertainment agency?

302
00:21:33,785 --> 00:21:35,995
Are you a casting director?

303
00:21:36,079 --> 00:21:37,119
I guess.

304
00:21:37,539 --> 00:21:39,919
She is quite attractive,
so I wanted to meet her.

305
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,880
She can't be in show business.
She's really weird.

306
00:21:42,961 --> 00:21:44,671
What's weird about her?

307
00:21:44,963 --> 00:21:46,593
She's soft in the head.

308
00:21:46,673 --> 00:21:48,553
No, she's not crazy. She sees ghosts.

309
00:21:48,633 --> 00:21:49,763
That's right.

310
00:21:50,385 --> 00:21:51,335
Ghosts?

311
00:21:51,428 --> 00:21:53,218
Yes, she sees ghosts.

312
00:21:53,596 --> 00:21:55,386
Everyone in our schools knows.

313
00:21:56,808 --> 00:21:59,478
You shouldn't make up rumors
about your friend like that.

314
00:21:59,561 --> 00:22:02,311
I'm telling the truth.
She talks to herself.

315
00:22:02,397 --> 00:22:04,607
She follows someone when there is nobody.

316
00:22:05,734 --> 00:22:08,324
She follows ghosts?

317
00:22:13,533 --> 00:22:14,833
That's interesting.

318
00:22:25,754 --> 00:22:29,014
Mr. Kim, I looked at the new menu.

319
00:22:29,090 --> 00:22:31,470
You changed the name of
our signature cocktail, Tears,

320
00:22:31,551 --> 00:22:33,011
to Tear Wine.

321
00:22:33,094 --> 00:22:35,974
Ms. Jang said it was too pretentious.

322
00:22:36,890 --> 00:22:38,060
Why? It was a good name.

323
00:22:38,141 --> 00:22:40,981
Tears and cheers.

324
00:22:41,061 --> 00:22:43,101
It has a nice ring to it.

325
00:22:43,188 --> 00:22:46,228
A Harvard graduate like you
thinks it's not bad, right?

326
00:22:46,649 --> 00:22:48,609
Ms. Jang's picking on me for no reason.

327
00:22:48,693 --> 00:22:50,363
It's the signature cocktail of our bar,

328
00:22:50,445 --> 00:22:52,195
so I think you should work on it
a bit more.

329
00:22:52,614 --> 00:22:55,334
Something like Angel's Tears
or Devil's Tears.

330
00:22:55,408 --> 00:22:58,118
You think so? Angel and Devil?

331
00:22:59,079 --> 00:23:00,709
I will make a note and give it to you.

332
00:23:00,997 --> 00:23:04,747
Harvard knows how to teach
their students properly.

333
00:23:10,173 --> 00:23:13,723
What are the guests doing
in the middle of the day?

334
00:23:13,885 --> 00:23:16,965
They are those who were killed
and buried secretly.

335
00:23:17,055 --> 00:23:19,635
I heard we had those guests.

336
00:23:20,391 --> 00:23:21,681
I heard the killer was caught.

337
00:23:21,768 --> 00:23:23,558
That's what I heard too.

338
00:23:23,645 --> 00:23:26,395
But Ms. Fourth Choice keeps saying
something is not right.

339
00:23:32,445 --> 00:23:35,155
<i>I don't think the man
the police caught is the culprit.</i>

340
00:23:36,116 --> 00:23:38,116
There was a ghost in this car too.

341
00:23:38,493 --> 00:23:40,753
The owner of this car is suspicious.

342
00:23:42,997 --> 00:23:45,997
81GI 0963

343
00:23:49,003 --> 00:23:51,593
Yu-na, you're still too young.

344
00:23:51,673 --> 00:23:53,633
You shouldn't get involved
in a violent crime like this.

345
00:23:53,716 --> 00:23:55,716
I agree. You should concentrate on school.

346
00:23:56,511 --> 00:24:00,771
Then, let me finish the sketch
I've been drawing.

347
00:24:01,432 --> 00:24:02,982
I'll show it to you when I finish it.

348
00:24:03,476 --> 00:24:05,266
I'll look into it if there's any problem.

349
00:24:05,353 --> 00:24:06,603
So you have to tell me.

350
00:24:06,688 --> 00:24:07,728
Okay.

351
00:24:12,986 --> 00:24:14,236
REQUEST FOR SPECIAL SERVICE

352
00:24:14,487 --> 00:24:16,867
They are the additional service requests
we have received today.

353
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:18,450
Oh, dear.

354
00:24:20,368 --> 00:24:22,198
It's such a bother.

355
00:24:29,836 --> 00:24:32,086
You probably saw the flowers.
Why aren't you saying anything?

356
00:24:32,172 --> 00:24:34,472
Have you all decided to get on the bus
to the afterlife?

357
00:24:35,425 --> 00:24:37,465
We are preparing ourselves for the worst.

358
00:24:37,719 --> 00:24:38,719
And I...

359
00:24:39,554 --> 00:24:43,814
will leave after I see
that family completely destroyed.

360
00:24:49,647 --> 00:24:51,477
You told me your daughter had to die

361
00:24:52,317 --> 00:24:54,277
for the family to carry on
their family line.

362
00:24:58,239 --> 00:25:00,029
No matter how impatient you feel,

363
00:25:01,201 --> 00:25:03,581
you must not do what you did 42 years ago.

364
00:25:07,999 --> 00:25:10,209
If you become an evil ghost and vanish,

365
00:25:10,293 --> 00:25:11,633
your 200 years

366
00:25:12,795 --> 00:25:16,215
of hard work at this hotel
will go down the drain.

367
00:25:18,801 --> 00:25:23,141
My grudge is so deep
that I don't care about those years.

368
00:25:30,313 --> 00:25:32,483
There will be a lunar eclipse soon.

369
00:25:32,815 --> 00:25:33,815
Yes.

370
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:37,360
I hear the moon will be covered
for quite a while this time.

371
00:25:38,154 --> 00:25:39,454
I'll prepare for it.

372
00:25:56,673 --> 00:25:57,513
Sir.

373
00:25:59,217 --> 00:26:01,087
Do you need anything?

374
00:26:01,761 --> 00:26:04,101
I'm thirsty.

375
00:26:04,264 --> 00:26:06,144
I'll bring something to drink
to your room.

376
00:26:06,349 --> 00:26:07,389
This way.

377
00:26:24,492 --> 00:26:26,742
A long lunar eclipse...

378
00:27:06,951 --> 00:27:10,001
Mr. Koo Chan-sung,
we need you to come with us.

379
00:27:29,390 --> 00:27:30,520
We brought him.

380
00:27:35,271 --> 00:27:36,481
Come closer.

381
00:27:42,195 --> 00:27:44,945
Who are you, and why did you look for me?

382
00:27:54,207 --> 00:27:55,787
Do you recognize me?

383
00:27:56,292 --> 00:27:58,672
Of course.
I even saw you on today's morning paper.

384
00:28:01,172 --> 00:28:02,802
I've been admiring you.

385
00:28:03,466 --> 00:28:06,086
But why did you call for me?

386
00:28:06,219 --> 00:28:08,679
I hear you're working at a hotel
that's registered

387
00:28:08,971 --> 00:28:10,771
at the Jung-gu District Office.

388
00:28:14,560 --> 00:28:16,400
Yes, that's right.

389
00:28:16,896 --> 00:28:20,476
Will you take me to that hotel?

390
00:28:21,025 --> 00:28:22,855
I'd like to meet with the owner.

391
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:25,660
Do you know...

392
00:28:27,115 --> 00:28:28,115
my boss?

393
00:28:28,241 --> 00:28:30,871
Hotel del Luna's Ms. Jang Man-wol.

394
00:28:36,791 --> 00:28:38,131
I used to be

395
00:28:38,835 --> 00:28:41,415
a manager who served Ms. Jang
at the hotel.

396
00:28:58,521 --> 00:29:00,401
Didn't you get off work early today?

397
00:29:00,523 --> 00:29:02,653
I brought a pleasant guest.

398
00:29:09,741 --> 00:29:10,871
Ji Hyeon-jung,

399
00:29:11,075 --> 00:29:13,325
do you still skip work
and leave the front desk unattended?

400
00:29:13,870 --> 00:29:15,710
Ms. Hwang!

401
00:29:17,540 --> 00:29:19,250
Goodness.

402
00:29:20,042 --> 00:29:21,462
What brings you here?

403
00:29:23,504 --> 00:29:26,094
You're not dead, are you?

404
00:29:26,174 --> 00:29:28,554
You still can't tell the difference?
I'm alive.

405
00:29:28,634 --> 00:29:30,184
You scared me.

406
00:29:31,929 --> 00:29:34,769
By the way,
should I call you President Hwang now?

407
00:29:34,849 --> 00:29:36,349
I'm only a candidate for now.

408
00:29:40,772 --> 00:29:42,942
Mr. Kim. Ms. Choe.

409
00:29:43,107 --> 00:29:44,687
Ms. Hwang is here.

410
00:29:44,776 --> 00:29:48,356
My goodness. You two are still here.

411
00:29:48,446 --> 00:29:49,566
Ms. Hwang.

412
00:29:50,531 --> 00:29:51,951
It's been a long time.

413
00:29:52,450 --> 00:29:53,660
It's been a while.

414
00:29:53,951 --> 00:29:55,911
Has it been over 30 years
since we last met?

415
00:29:55,995 --> 00:29:57,365
You've gotten old.

416
00:29:57,455 --> 00:29:59,365
You still make
such straightforward comments.

417
00:30:01,626 --> 00:30:04,796
Do you have a lot of guests
at the hotel right now?

418
00:30:04,879 --> 00:30:06,459
I can't see anyone else

419
00:30:06,547 --> 00:30:08,377
other than the hotel's employees now.

420
00:30:11,719 --> 00:30:13,049
There are a few.

421
00:30:14,847 --> 00:30:17,057
There's Ms. Jang.

422
00:30:37,286 --> 00:30:39,576
Your hotel has become so big.

423
00:30:39,664 --> 00:30:41,374
It's all thanks to you, Mun-suk.

424
00:30:41,707 --> 00:30:43,457
Thanks to the money you made back then,

425
00:30:43,543 --> 00:30:45,963
we were able to move to Myeong-dong
and got big.

426
00:30:47,839 --> 00:30:49,419
It seems you've become a big shot too.

427
00:30:49,590 --> 00:30:51,180
I saw you a lot on the phone.

428
00:30:51,843 --> 00:30:54,143
I hear you'll become a president
of somewhere big soon.

429
00:30:54,762 --> 00:30:56,312
I'm just a candidate for now.

430
00:30:56,597 --> 00:30:58,677
I'm thankful you let me free.

431
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:02,810
Do you think I let you go
because I wanted to?

432
00:31:03,396 --> 00:31:06,896
Mago thought someone talented like you
shouldn't be tied up to a place like this.

433
00:31:06,983 --> 00:31:08,943
She gave you the medicine behind my back,

434
00:31:09,026 --> 00:31:12,066
and you couldn't see ghosts anymore.
So I had no choice but to let you go.

435
00:31:12,572 --> 00:31:15,532
I wish you had stayed
for a few more years back then

436
00:31:15,616 --> 00:31:16,986
and made more money for me.

437
00:31:17,076 --> 00:31:19,996
I'd have quite a lot of land
in Gangnam right now.

438
00:31:20,788 --> 00:31:22,998
Thanks to the experience here,

439
00:31:23,374 --> 00:31:25,004
the way I see the world

440
00:31:25,084 --> 00:31:27,924
and the things I value
have changed greatly.

441
00:31:29,213 --> 00:31:32,093
Sure. It seems like
you are doing a lot of good work.

442
00:31:32,842 --> 00:31:34,342
Why are you here anyway?

443
00:31:35,887 --> 00:31:37,847
I have a favor to ask of you.

444
00:31:40,141 --> 00:31:41,391
A favor?

445
00:31:43,436 --> 00:31:44,726
Of course.

446
00:31:45,229 --> 00:31:47,609
I know there's nothing
you would miss here.

447
00:31:47,940 --> 00:31:50,110
You must be here
because you want something.

448
00:31:50,735 --> 00:31:51,775
Oh, right.

449
00:31:52,653 --> 00:31:57,073
I brought a present
that might suit you well.

450
00:31:58,910 --> 00:32:00,200
Gosh.

451
00:32:00,745 --> 00:32:03,495
You shouldn't have brought such a thing.

452
00:32:06,918 --> 00:32:09,708
Oh, my god.

453
00:32:11,547 --> 00:32:13,087
Okay. What's the favor you want?

454
00:32:14,008 --> 00:32:16,928
It's something trivial,
but very important.

455
00:32:18,930 --> 00:32:22,980
We're getting
another big lunar eclipse after 39 years.

456
00:32:26,854 --> 00:32:29,984
This country was seeing
an economic revival at that time.

457
00:32:30,066 --> 00:32:31,726
And thanks to Mun-suk's appearance,

458
00:32:31,943 --> 00:32:34,613
Ms. Jang was able to turn the poor
business into a successful one,

459
00:32:34,695 --> 00:32:38,775
laying the groundwork for the wealth
and luxury she's enjoying now.

460
00:32:38,866 --> 00:32:41,326
She worked here
for about seven to eight years.

461
00:32:41,452 --> 00:32:44,962
I never imagined such a person
would've worked here as a manager.

462
00:32:45,164 --> 00:32:48,964
Because Ms. Jang doesn't leave
any traces of the human managers

463
00:32:49,251 --> 00:32:51,091
who used to work here.

464
00:32:53,547 --> 00:32:54,717
However,

465
00:32:55,675 --> 00:32:58,835
I wonder why she came here when she has
such a big event happening soon.

466
00:32:59,679 --> 00:33:02,599
We're going to take human guests?
Is that possible?

467
00:33:02,765 --> 00:33:05,265
Yes, because a lunar eclipse is coming.

468
00:33:05,434 --> 00:33:07,194
Are things different with a lunar eclipse?

469
00:33:07,269 --> 00:33:08,979
When the moon's covered during an eclipse,

470
00:33:09,063 --> 00:33:12,023
the Guest House of the Moon's presence
is exposed.

471
00:33:12,358 --> 00:33:15,438
That's why we get quite a few human guests
during eclipses.

472
00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:19,491
Even humans are able to see our ghost
guests when they come into our hotel.

473
00:33:19,657 --> 00:33:22,157
So, do we accept human guests
on the day of the lunar eclipse?

474
00:33:22,243 --> 00:33:24,333
The front desk turns them away, of course.

475
00:33:24,662 --> 00:33:25,752
But...

476
00:33:26,622 --> 00:33:28,922
Did that happen in 1981?

477
00:33:29,125 --> 00:33:31,625
When Mun-suk was here
during a lunar eclipse,

478
00:33:31,794 --> 00:33:34,464
some newlyweds stayed at our hotel.

479
00:33:36,549 --> 00:33:39,719
I'm sorry, I didn't realize
it's past the curfew.

480
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,970
-I'm sorry.
-Is it this way?

481
00:33:42,054 --> 00:33:43,264
Yes. That way.

482
00:33:43,597 --> 00:33:45,307
HOTEL DEL LUNA

483
00:33:45,391 --> 00:33:47,271
I think this is a hotel.

484
00:33:50,271 --> 00:33:53,191
The lunar eclipse better end soon.

485
00:33:57,361 --> 00:33:59,111
-Excuse me.
-Do you have a room?

486
00:34:03,868 --> 00:34:04,988
Newlyweds?

487
00:34:05,578 --> 00:34:08,368
They came to Seoul for their honeymoon,
and now it's past curfew.

488
00:34:08,539 --> 00:34:09,829
If we turn them away now,

489
00:34:09,915 --> 00:34:12,375
they'll have to spend
their first night at the police station.

490
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:13,630
I feel bad for them.

491
00:34:17,673 --> 00:34:18,973
Let them in, then.

492
00:34:35,733 --> 00:34:36,943
This is your room.

493
00:34:40,112 --> 00:34:41,242
Please go in.

494
00:34:41,489 --> 00:34:42,989
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

495
00:34:43,240 --> 00:34:44,410
Thank you so much.

496
00:34:51,874 --> 00:34:55,884
<i>The couple spent
their first night at our hotel.</i>

497
00:34:56,587 --> 00:34:59,797
<i>At that night, a human baby was conceived
for the first time</i>

498
00:35:00,257 --> 00:35:01,877
<i>at this ghost hotel.</i>

499
00:35:04,178 --> 00:35:08,558
And that baby grew up to be
Korea's most talented soccer player.

500
00:35:21,904 --> 00:35:22,914
Really?

501
00:35:23,614 --> 00:35:25,744
He got conceived here?

502
00:35:25,825 --> 00:35:29,075
Yes, apparently. I was shocked too
when I heard about it earlier.

503
00:35:30,496 --> 00:35:34,166
Anyway, he's going to become
Mun-suk's son-in-law.

504
00:35:34,250 --> 00:35:36,210
-Really?
-She went to meet her future in-laws

505
00:35:36,293 --> 00:35:39,463
and met the newlywed couple.
They were all so surprised.

506
00:35:40,256 --> 00:35:41,966
What an interesting coincidence.

507
00:35:42,758 --> 00:35:46,718
But then again,
this place is full of unimaginable things.

508
00:35:46,929 --> 00:35:49,599
I guess it's natural that the baby
turned out to be someone special.

509
00:35:49,682 --> 00:35:51,852
She wants us to let her daughter
and future son-in-law

510
00:35:52,017 --> 00:35:55,977
stay here for one night so they can
also experience the same thing.

511
00:35:57,773 --> 00:36:01,443
Then, are we going to let them stay
in the room that the King stayed in?

512
00:36:01,527 --> 00:36:03,947
No, they're humans.

513
00:36:04,029 --> 00:36:05,779
They should stay in Room 404.

514
00:36:06,699 --> 00:36:07,869
Room 404?

515
00:36:15,207 --> 00:36:18,037
<i>But no one can check out of that room.</i>

516
00:36:19,211 --> 00:36:22,211
The only way you can check out
of our hotel is head for the afterlife.

517
00:36:22,590 --> 00:36:25,340
Then how are they supposed to check out
of Room 404?

518
00:36:27,761 --> 00:36:29,681
Are you worried about them?

519
00:36:33,851 --> 00:36:36,311
Then why don't you go in there
and check for yourself?

520
00:37:21,649 --> 00:37:23,279
On the night of this year's lunar eclipse,

521
00:37:24,485 --> 00:37:26,525
we'll be welcoming human guests.

522
00:37:28,572 --> 00:37:31,202
They're newlyweds.
It'll be their honeymoon.

523
00:37:35,663 --> 00:37:38,173
They made an official reservation
this time,

524
00:37:38,249 --> 00:37:39,579
so get ready to treat them well.

525
00:37:39,667 --> 00:37:40,747
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

526
00:37:45,756 --> 00:37:49,756
We need to get food and decorations
that are fit for humans.

527
00:37:49,843 --> 00:37:51,853
I'm excited to hear
that we'll be getting human guests.

528
00:37:51,929 --> 00:37:54,059
But where's our manager?

529
00:37:54,139 --> 00:37:55,639
He went inside Room 404.

530
00:37:57,142 --> 00:37:59,482
Then I guess he won't be
returning tonight.

531
00:38:00,354 --> 00:38:04,024
Whatever the case, I'm really excited.

532
00:38:15,452 --> 00:38:16,542
Veronica.

533
00:38:17,663 --> 00:38:19,083
Are you in Wai Tan in Shanghai?

534
00:38:19,164 --> 00:38:22,134
<i>Yes, I was in a meeting,
but I came out to eat lunch now.</i>

535
00:38:22,334 --> 00:38:26,014
-<i>Sanchez, I'm so upset at you</i>.
-Why? Why are you upset?

536
00:38:26,088 --> 00:38:28,668
<i>I miss you so much.</i>

537
00:38:28,924 --> 00:38:33,144
<i>You really make it hard
for me to focus on work.</i>

538
00:38:33,220 --> 00:38:34,930
<i>I'm going to scold you.</i>

539
00:38:35,014 --> 00:38:38,774
Veronica, I can't wait to meet you
so you can scold me.

540
00:38:41,353 --> 00:38:42,403
Veronica.

541
00:38:42,896 --> 00:38:46,816
I found a way to get scolded by you
forever. You can look forward to it.

542
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:51,070
<i>Gosh, what are you
going to surprise me with this time?</i>

543
00:38:51,989 --> 00:38:54,989
I can't tell you. You can come here
and check for yourself.

544
00:38:55,284 --> 00:38:56,374
Chan-sung's here.

545
00:38:57,411 --> 00:38:58,541
Say hello.

546
00:38:59,496 --> 00:39:01,326
<i>Hey, Chan-sung.</i>

547
00:39:01,749 --> 00:39:02,829
Hi, Veronica.

548
00:39:04,293 --> 00:39:05,923
Veronica, I'll call you later.

549
00:39:06,211 --> 00:39:09,671
<i>I love you. Goodbye, my love.</i>

550
00:39:10,341 --> 00:39:11,381
Bye.

551
00:39:12,384 --> 00:39:14,394
-Is Veronica coming to Korea?
-Yes.

552
00:39:14,928 --> 00:39:17,678
She's in Shanghai right now.
She's going to come in two days.

553
00:39:18,098 --> 00:39:19,218
So I've been thinking...

554
00:39:24,063 --> 00:39:26,733
I'm planning to do
something really important.

555
00:39:27,399 --> 00:39:29,359
And I'm thinking about doing it
at your hotel.

556
00:39:30,944 --> 00:39:31,784
My hotel?

557
00:39:31,862 --> 00:39:34,282
Veronica's been to all kinds
of hotels all over the world.

558
00:39:34,365 --> 00:39:36,525
When I told her that you work
at a really special hotel,

559
00:39:36,617 --> 00:39:38,827
she wanted to take a look.
I'm also quite curious.

560
00:39:39,828 --> 00:39:41,458
No, you can't do it at my hotel.

561
00:39:42,164 --> 00:39:45,544
Chan-sung, you're not exactly working
at a decent hotel, are you?

562
00:39:45,876 --> 00:39:47,246
-What?
-You had to invite someone

563
00:39:47,336 --> 00:39:48,796
to our house to sell a painting.

564
00:39:48,879 --> 00:39:50,839
And Man-wol even asked me
to sell her horses.

565
00:39:51,048 --> 00:39:52,878
Are you guys struggling financially?

566
00:39:55,594 --> 00:39:56,684
Yes, it's pretty bad.

567
00:39:56,762 --> 00:39:58,892
My goodness.

568
00:40:00,974 --> 00:40:03,444
Chan-sung, let me know
if you're having a hard time.

569
00:40:03,852 --> 00:40:06,692
You can't just endure everything
with love.

570
00:40:07,314 --> 00:40:08,324
Okay?

571
00:40:09,358 --> 00:40:10,278
Okay.

572
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:13,360
Fine, let's break up.

573
00:40:13,695 --> 00:40:14,905
My gosh.

574
00:40:15,531 --> 00:40:17,121
Mi-ra's fighting all the time.

575
00:40:17,199 --> 00:40:19,279
She and the cop must've been enemies
in their past lives.

576
00:40:19,368 --> 00:40:20,368
They fight all the time.

577
00:40:20,452 --> 00:40:22,292
But she always goes out to meet him.

578
00:40:22,913 --> 00:40:25,253
What? You're not the only one who's busy.

579
00:40:25,499 --> 00:40:27,079
I'm busy too.

580
00:40:27,835 --> 00:40:29,665
You talk like your job is
to save the world.

581
00:40:29,753 --> 00:40:31,553
You think you're a superhero or something?

582
00:40:32,464 --> 00:40:33,474
What?

583
00:40:35,426 --> 00:40:37,086
They were enemies in their past lives.

584
00:40:40,139 --> 00:40:43,559
Sanchez, let's all eat together
when Veronica comes to Korea.

585
00:40:43,851 --> 00:40:45,441
-She's coming in two days, right?
-Yes.

586
00:40:46,562 --> 00:40:48,482
-That's the day of the lunar eclipse.
-Yes, I know.

587
00:40:48,564 --> 00:40:51,864
I was planning on watching
the lunar eclipse at the rooftop bar

588
00:40:51,942 --> 00:40:53,902
in your hotel that you bragged about.

589
00:40:54,069 --> 00:40:55,529
Maybe next time.

590
00:40:57,197 --> 00:40:58,197
I'm sorry.

591
00:40:59,950 --> 00:41:03,540
They could get startled
if they run into other hotel guests.

592
00:41:03,620 --> 00:41:05,500
So we should empty the adjacent rooms.

593
00:41:05,581 --> 00:41:08,541
We already informed the guests
on the fourth floor.

594
00:41:08,625 --> 00:41:10,165
We're moving them to other rooms.

595
00:41:21,013 --> 00:41:22,723
You really are well prepared.

596
00:41:24,558 --> 00:41:26,058
The dinner menu is great.

597
00:41:27,436 --> 00:41:28,976
What kind of drink are you going to...

598
00:41:30,105 --> 00:41:31,685
Are you going to serve them these drinks?

599
00:41:31,773 --> 00:41:35,403
I took your advice
and created my own signature menu.

600
00:41:35,611 --> 00:41:36,951
They're the Angel and Devil.

601
00:41:38,697 --> 00:41:39,737
It's incredible.

602
00:41:40,073 --> 00:41:43,493
But I'm not sure if humans will like them.

603
00:41:43,577 --> 00:41:44,827
Could you try them?

604
00:41:45,037 --> 00:41:46,037
Sure.

605
00:42:00,969 --> 00:42:03,719
Put half of them on the dinner table
and the other half in their room.

606
00:42:03,805 --> 00:42:04,715
Yes, sir.

607
00:42:09,102 --> 00:42:10,192
It's a bee.

608
00:42:12,439 --> 00:42:15,319
I guess the bee came along
since these are real flowers.

609
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:17,740
I guess we don't have
any bees or butterflies here

610
00:42:17,819 --> 00:42:20,109
since the flowers here are not real.

611
00:42:29,248 --> 00:42:30,328
By any chance,

612
00:42:31,083 --> 00:42:34,753
are there also bug ghosts
that look like fireflies?

613
00:42:34,836 --> 00:42:37,206
I've never heard of anything
called a bug ghost.

614
00:42:37,297 --> 00:42:38,967
Oh, I see.

615
00:42:41,426 --> 00:42:42,886
Then what was that?

616
00:42:42,970 --> 00:42:45,100
Should I put this bouquet in their room?

617
00:42:45,180 --> 00:42:46,270
Yes, sure.

618
00:42:46,723 --> 00:42:48,063
That one looks more romantic.

619
00:42:49,268 --> 00:42:50,268
Wait.

620
00:42:59,194 --> 00:43:01,204
I'd like to put one in my office.

621
00:43:03,031 --> 00:43:04,071
Please follow me.

622
00:43:21,550 --> 00:43:24,340
God... I'm so tired.

623
00:43:34,605 --> 00:43:36,975
You got a lot of special requests
again today, didn't you?

624
00:43:37,065 --> 00:43:39,735
You're all so excited
about those human guests.

625
00:43:39,860 --> 00:43:42,650
I'm the only one
who's taking care of our actual guests.

626
00:43:43,530 --> 00:43:47,780
My gosh, the day feels so long.

627
00:43:48,285 --> 00:43:50,655
My goodness, I'm so tired.

628
00:43:52,706 --> 00:43:54,826
Then here's something to wake you up.

629
00:43:59,338 --> 00:44:01,548
This is a real flower, so it smells nice.

630
00:44:04,217 --> 00:44:06,387
We have tons of flowers in our garden.

631
00:44:06,470 --> 00:44:08,510
None of them are real.

632
00:44:08,930 --> 00:44:11,930
No, wait. Your flowers are real.

633
00:44:14,519 --> 00:44:16,979
That tree of yours is
filled with beautiful flowers.

634
00:44:17,064 --> 00:44:18,524
What's with you?

635
00:44:19,149 --> 00:44:20,359
Are you showing off?

636
00:44:20,442 --> 00:44:21,692
I'm entitled to show off.

637
00:44:21,777 --> 00:44:23,697
The flowers bloomed
the moment I hugged you.

638
00:44:24,488 --> 00:44:26,528
If I knew this was going to happen,
I should've hugged you

639
00:44:26,615 --> 00:44:28,365
instead of buying you champagne.

640
00:44:31,620 --> 00:44:33,250
What are you doing?

641
00:44:33,789 --> 00:44:35,039
I never asked you to hug me.

642
00:44:35,290 --> 00:44:37,040
Are you crazy?

643
00:44:38,001 --> 00:44:39,591
I was asking for the phone.

644
00:44:43,548 --> 00:44:45,298
Okay, here. I'll let you hug me.

645
00:44:48,345 --> 00:44:49,925
Forget it.

646
00:44:50,055 --> 00:44:52,845
You arrogant, greedy fraud from Harvard--

647
00:44:56,770 --> 00:44:58,110
You look so pretty.

648
00:45:00,273 --> 00:45:02,573
I put the additional special requests
on your desk.

649
00:45:02,776 --> 00:45:06,106
You should get back to work
after you get some rest.

650
00:45:26,299 --> 00:45:27,429
Darn it.

651
00:45:36,017 --> 00:45:38,147
<i>I won't let you vanish.</i>

652
00:45:39,146 --> 00:45:40,186
<i>Trust me.</i>

653
00:45:58,915 --> 00:46:00,125
It's real.

654
00:46:01,334 --> 00:46:02,344
You,

655
00:46:03,170 --> 00:46:05,340
I'm going easy on you
because you have a soft heart.

656
00:46:51,635 --> 00:46:53,175
The lunar eclipse has begun.

657
00:46:53,720 --> 00:46:57,270
There will be special guests
coming tonight.

658
00:46:58,141 --> 00:47:01,021
Please do your best
to get ready for the guests.

659
00:47:10,070 --> 00:47:11,910
Everyone seems quite excited.

660
00:47:12,030 --> 00:47:13,450
As the moon gets covered,

661
00:47:13,782 --> 00:47:16,702
they can feel the hotel's presence
is shown to the world.

662
00:47:17,369 --> 00:47:19,699
And human guests are coming as well.

663
00:47:20,539 --> 00:47:24,289
That makes them
feel like they're alive again.

664
00:47:37,264 --> 00:47:38,644
Welcome.

665
00:47:39,391 --> 00:47:41,271
You made a reservation, right?

666
00:47:41,351 --> 00:47:43,021
How long has it been
since you passed away--

667
00:47:47,274 --> 00:47:49,154
I mean, how long has it been
since you got married?

668
00:47:54,155 --> 00:47:56,315
Right, you got married today!

669
00:47:57,033 --> 00:47:58,203
Congratulations.

670
00:47:58,702 --> 00:48:00,202
Please follow me this way.

671
00:48:11,214 --> 00:48:13,304
We'll take your luggage to your room.

672
00:48:13,550 --> 00:48:15,300
You can enjoy your meals first.

673
00:48:17,679 --> 00:48:21,179
These cocktails, Tears, are
our hotel's signature cocktails.

674
00:48:22,767 --> 00:48:25,187
This beautiful one is called
the Angel's Tears.

675
00:48:27,147 --> 00:48:29,897
And this one is called the Devil's Tears.

676
00:48:48,209 --> 00:48:49,499
Why are you so happy?

677
00:48:50,503 --> 00:48:54,053
I hated looking at the full moon.

678
00:48:54,132 --> 00:48:56,512
But look, it's all gone now.

679
00:48:56,676 --> 00:48:58,716
It feels so good watching that.

680
00:48:59,012 --> 00:49:02,772
This is my favorite moment ever.

681
00:49:07,270 --> 00:49:08,770
The whole moon is covered now.

682
00:49:09,397 --> 00:49:12,227
The moon will be different
when it comes out again.

683
00:49:12,317 --> 00:49:14,937
Perhaps it'll know how to be kind
and cut down on spending.

684
00:49:17,447 --> 00:49:19,947
After our human guests
check out of the hotel,

685
00:49:20,116 --> 00:49:22,326
would you like to go out
and see the new, kind moon?

686
00:49:22,535 --> 00:49:23,615
You evil moon.

687
00:49:24,037 --> 00:49:27,167
Do you want to die, Chan-sung?

688
00:49:27,499 --> 00:49:28,669
I'll take that as a yes.

689
00:49:28,958 --> 00:49:30,208
This is why I love my name.

690
00:49:30,335 --> 00:49:32,665
I love how it means "yes."
It's like everyone agrees with me.

691
00:49:33,755 --> 00:49:34,795
It's perfect.

692
00:49:35,423 --> 00:49:37,433
Zero looks like a circle.
And "Koo" means a circle.

693
00:49:38,677 --> 00:49:39,757
Koo Chan-sung.

694
00:49:41,221 --> 00:49:44,471
Sure, Mr. Zeroth Choice,

695
00:49:44,557 --> 00:49:46,767
your name is Mr. Okay Koo now.

696
00:49:47,686 --> 00:49:49,016
What do you mean?

697
00:49:49,104 --> 00:49:51,274
My English name is Andrew.

698
00:49:51,356 --> 00:49:54,776
Chan-sung isn't just okay,
it means "agreement."

699
00:49:54,859 --> 00:49:57,449
Agree, Andrew, whatever.

700
00:49:57,529 --> 00:49:59,949
You're just Okay Koo to me.

701
00:50:00,031 --> 00:50:01,031
Okay?

702
00:50:04,452 --> 00:50:06,912
Okay Koo,
the lunar eclipse is finally complete.

703
00:50:12,877 --> 00:50:13,917
You're right.

704
00:50:30,186 --> 00:50:33,016
This sign means it's yours, right?

705
00:50:34,357 --> 00:50:35,357
Yes.

706
00:50:53,001 --> 00:50:54,501
I wonder if he was waiting for her.

707
00:51:04,721 --> 00:51:05,721
Ms. Jang.

708
00:51:07,557 --> 00:51:11,057
Our guests would like
to go into their room now.

709
00:51:12,312 --> 00:51:14,652
Okay, the lunar eclipse is complete.

710
00:51:14,731 --> 00:51:17,531
It's perfect. Take them to Room 404.

711
00:51:17,817 --> 00:51:18,737
Yes.

712
00:51:34,584 --> 00:51:35,754
Once you go inside,

713
00:51:35,835 --> 00:51:39,125
please don't come out of the room
until you check out.

714
00:51:39,214 --> 00:51:41,634
I already heard about this room
from my parents.

715
00:51:42,842 --> 00:51:44,892
Have a good night then.

716
00:52:07,450 --> 00:52:09,370
A world-famous soccer player
was conceived here.

717
00:52:09,452 --> 00:52:10,702
Who do you think will be next?

718
00:52:10,787 --> 00:52:13,117
You've been a kid for 70 years,
so you wouldn't know this.

719
00:52:13,206 --> 00:52:15,206
But things like this
don't happen just overnight.

720
00:52:15,291 --> 00:52:18,631
I know that it doesn't happen
just overnight.

721
00:52:23,633 --> 00:52:25,843
Why are you laughing?

722
00:52:30,181 --> 00:52:31,721
I know it all.

723
00:52:31,891 --> 00:52:32,891
Really?

724
00:52:34,394 --> 00:52:36,194
Don't just assume
that I don't know things.

725
00:52:36,312 --> 00:52:37,812
We're talking about lives here.

726
00:52:37,897 --> 00:52:39,857
It's not a conversation
a Grim Ripper could jump into.

727
00:52:43,903 --> 00:52:45,203
I hope

728
00:52:45,280 --> 00:52:47,700
that a great scholar will be conceived
this time.

729
00:52:47,782 --> 00:52:49,872
I hope the child will receive
a Nobel Prize.

730
00:52:49,951 --> 00:52:52,041
I hope that triplets will be conceived

731
00:52:52,120 --> 00:52:54,160
so that they'd win three Nobel Prizes.

732
00:52:54,622 --> 00:52:58,382
All the guests and employees at the hotel
are rooting for Room 404 right now.

733
00:53:00,795 --> 00:53:02,505
Veronica hasn't arrived yet?

734
00:53:03,548 --> 00:53:05,968
I waited for her,
thinking that her flight was delayed,

735
00:53:06,050 --> 00:53:07,720
but the flight was never delayed.

736
00:53:07,802 --> 00:53:09,222
She's not even picking up her phone.

737
00:53:13,600 --> 00:53:14,600
Chan-sung,

738
00:53:15,184 --> 00:53:18,354
do you think Veronica knew
I was going to propose

739
00:53:18,438 --> 00:53:20,568
and is avoiding me
because she's feeling pressured?

740
00:53:21,441 --> 00:53:23,281
Veronica loves you more than you love her.

741
00:53:23,359 --> 00:53:26,239
No, I love her so much more.

742
00:53:29,490 --> 00:53:32,450
Veronica has never broken
any promises with me.

743
00:53:34,412 --> 00:53:36,582
I just got a text.
It must be from Veronica.

744
00:53:36,664 --> 00:53:38,124
I'll call you later.

745
00:54:12,367 --> 00:54:13,407
Sanchez.

746
00:54:14,744 --> 00:54:15,794
Sanchez!

747
00:54:17,205 --> 00:54:18,285
Sanchez!

748
00:54:20,124 --> 00:54:21,424
An accident? What happened?

749
00:54:21,501 --> 00:54:23,421
Veronica got hurt.

750
00:54:23,670 --> 00:54:25,630
I think she got into a car accident
in Shanghai.

751
00:54:26,547 --> 00:54:27,717
I have to go now.

752
00:54:27,799 --> 00:54:29,219
How badly is she hurt?

753
00:54:29,300 --> 00:54:31,590
I have to go and see.

754
00:54:31,970 --> 00:54:33,850
-I'm sure she'll be fine.
-Yes.

755
00:54:34,681 --> 00:54:37,771
Hey, I have to stay there
until she gets better.

756
00:54:37,892 --> 00:54:38,892
Okay.

757
00:54:41,646 --> 00:54:43,106
Where's my car key?

758
00:54:52,949 --> 00:54:54,199
I have to go.

759
00:55:02,166 --> 00:55:03,576
Even if you go there,

760
00:55:05,962 --> 00:55:07,092
you won't be able to see her.

761
00:55:08,673 --> 00:55:11,553
Hey, don't say that.

762
00:55:12,301 --> 00:55:13,681
You won't be able to see her.

763
00:55:18,891 --> 00:55:19,931
It's too late.

764
00:55:21,769 --> 00:55:23,229
What's with you?

765
00:55:24,355 --> 00:55:25,895
It's not too late!

766
00:55:26,441 --> 00:55:28,031
If I go now, I can see her.

767
00:55:42,290 --> 00:55:43,330
Sanchez.

768
00:55:44,625 --> 00:55:45,995
I'll let you see her.

769
00:55:46,711 --> 00:55:47,751
What?

770
00:55:48,171 --> 00:55:49,711
If you come to my hotel now,

771
00:55:50,715 --> 00:55:52,085
you can meet her.

772
00:55:54,052 --> 00:55:57,062
Hey. What the hell are you talking about?

773
00:55:57,764 --> 00:56:00,354
Do you trust me? We don't have much time.

774
00:56:00,433 --> 00:56:02,443
You won't be able to see her
if you're late.

775
00:56:29,712 --> 00:56:30,712
Mr. Koo.

776
00:56:31,339 --> 00:56:33,549
There is a lady guest
who'll come in right after us.

777
00:56:33,966 --> 00:56:36,336
We'll be waiting for her
at the Sky Lounge.

778
00:56:37,386 --> 00:56:38,846
Please bring her over

779
00:56:39,806 --> 00:56:40,846
after the beauty service.

780
00:56:41,140 --> 00:56:42,060
Sure.

781
00:57:15,466 --> 00:57:16,466
Let go of me.

782
00:57:17,301 --> 00:57:19,141
What are we going to do here?

783
00:57:19,262 --> 00:57:20,812
You'll see once you go out there.

784
00:57:21,139 --> 00:57:22,519
I'll tell you after you see this.

785
00:57:37,697 --> 00:57:39,987
Hey, how are you working here?

786
00:57:40,533 --> 00:57:42,293
This is a very special hotel.

787
00:57:42,952 --> 00:57:44,582
It's a hotel for the dead.

788
00:57:45,079 --> 00:57:46,119
What?

789
00:57:50,751 --> 00:57:52,211
I have no time to explain.

790
00:57:52,378 --> 00:57:55,668
You can see the dead
until the eclipse is over.

791
00:57:56,007 --> 00:57:57,007
So,

792
00:57:58,718 --> 00:58:00,508
you'll have only a little time

793
00:58:01,471 --> 00:58:02,891
to say goodbye to Veronica.

794
00:58:05,850 --> 00:58:06,850
What?

795
00:58:07,226 --> 00:58:09,806
Stop joking around.
How could she come here?

796
00:58:12,773 --> 00:58:14,073
Because she's dead.

797
00:58:25,620 --> 00:58:26,910
She is here.

798
00:58:28,873 --> 00:58:30,673
Sanchez, Veronica is dead.

799
00:59:32,228 --> 00:59:33,598
I'm sorry...

800
00:59:35,731 --> 00:59:37,901
I surprised you like this.

801
01:00:10,683 --> 01:00:12,233
Don't cry too much...

802
01:00:14,854 --> 01:00:16,814
for me.

803
01:00:20,818 --> 01:00:21,818
I lived

804
01:00:23,362 --> 01:00:25,992
a happy life thanks to you.

805
01:00:55,686 --> 01:00:58,606
My awfully handsome love.

806
01:01:02,610 --> 01:01:03,740
Goodbye.

807
01:02:22,565 --> 01:02:24,275
Mr. Koo's friend

808
01:02:24,984 --> 01:02:26,994
had to say goodbye to his love.

809
01:02:27,820 --> 01:02:31,410
Such a sudden death leaves
those left behind

810
01:02:32,074 --> 01:02:34,454
with great sorrow.

811
01:02:36,620 --> 01:02:38,910
I only see the dead these days,

812
01:02:41,000 --> 01:02:43,540
so it's been a while
since I saw the sorrow

813
01:02:45,171 --> 01:02:46,421
of the living.

814
01:03:42,978 --> 01:03:44,478
Yes, come in.

815
01:03:55,115 --> 01:03:57,325
Did you have a great night?

816
01:03:57,451 --> 01:04:00,831
Yes. We won't be able to forget
the time we spent

817
01:04:00,913 --> 01:04:02,873
in this hotel.

818
01:04:03,082 --> 01:04:06,002
Thank you. Take care then.

819
01:04:25,479 --> 01:04:27,399
It's exactly like what my parents told me.

820
01:04:28,107 --> 01:04:29,897
It's a hotel you can never find again.

821
01:04:30,985 --> 01:04:32,895
When we have a baby later,

822
01:04:33,445 --> 01:04:37,485
let's find the hotel and have the baby
go on their honeymoon there like we did.

823
01:04:38,868 --> 01:04:39,908
I'd like that.

824
01:05:19,825 --> 01:05:22,655
Veronica's funeral will be held in Italy.

825
01:05:22,870 --> 01:05:25,330
Sanchez will stay there for a while.

826
01:05:25,623 --> 01:05:27,633
I feel so sorry for Sanchez.

827
01:05:28,500 --> 01:05:31,090
He couldn't even see
his girlfriend's last moments.

828
01:05:32,087 --> 01:05:33,457
He didn't get to say goodbye.

829
01:05:34,173 --> 01:05:36,553
He saw her. He got to say goodbye too.

830
01:05:38,177 --> 01:05:40,347
He learned that death isn't the end,

831
01:05:41,430 --> 01:05:43,600
so I'm sure Sanchez will be able
to get through it.

832
01:05:45,184 --> 01:05:46,814
So he got to say goodbye.

833
01:05:49,772 --> 01:05:51,112
But how did he see her?

834
01:05:52,149 --> 01:05:53,819
Didn't she die in Shanghai?

835
01:05:56,904 --> 01:05:59,454
Gosh, this coffee smells so good.
You should have another.

836
01:06:27,101 --> 01:06:29,981
I'm sorry.

837
01:07:14,148 --> 01:07:15,438
She's really tailing me.

838
01:07:22,781 --> 01:07:25,331
Why would such a cute student follow me?

839
01:07:29,079 --> 01:07:30,289
I better ask her.

840
01:07:34,877 --> 01:07:37,877
I heard they really enjoyed their stay.

841
01:07:38,338 --> 01:07:39,718
Thank you.

842
01:07:42,301 --> 01:07:45,931
If you end up quitting your job
at Hotel del Luna, come look for me.

843
01:07:46,555 --> 01:07:50,305
Ms. Jang told me
that you're quite competent

844
01:07:50,601 --> 01:07:52,271
and recommended you to me.

845
01:07:53,729 --> 01:07:55,729
I don't think I'll be quitting.

846
01:07:57,191 --> 01:08:00,401
According to Ms. Jang,
you're going to quit soon.

847
01:08:04,698 --> 01:08:07,788
There's a guest
Chan-sung will have to send off himself.

848
01:08:08,494 --> 01:08:10,164
Once he sends off that guest,

849
01:08:12,081 --> 01:08:13,791
he'll probably leave this place.

850
01:08:18,128 --> 01:08:19,248
Did she say that?

851
01:08:19,713 --> 01:08:22,723
Did they come up with a new rule
for the hotel manager?

852
01:08:23,550 --> 01:08:27,510
Who is the last guest
you'll be sending off?

853
01:08:33,143 --> 01:08:34,853
It's someone...

854
01:08:37,064 --> 01:08:38,234
I like a lot.

855
01:08:46,824 --> 01:08:48,414
It'll be difficult for you.

856
01:08:54,081 --> 01:08:55,171
I think so.

857
01:08:59,169 --> 01:09:01,919
It's too hard for me to console myself...

858
01:09:06,135 --> 01:09:07,885
by saying I know it's coming.

859
01:09:51,388 --> 01:09:53,638
What were you doing? Were you sleeping?

860
01:09:56,727 --> 01:09:57,727
I'm awake.

861
01:09:58,687 --> 01:09:59,857
I'm looking at the moon.

862
01:10:02,316 --> 01:10:03,316
The moon?

863
01:10:04,526 --> 01:10:06,066
How can you see the moon during the day?

864
01:10:07,404 --> 01:10:08,414
I don't know.

865
01:10:12,409 --> 01:10:14,159
It must be pretty hard

866
01:10:15,204 --> 01:10:16,544
to miss something you can't see.

867
01:10:28,967 --> 01:10:29,967
Where are you?

868
01:10:32,304 --> 01:10:33,814
I'm on my way home.

869
01:10:34,932 --> 01:10:37,892
Wait at home. I'll come to see you.

870
01:10:56,119 --> 01:10:57,909
What is it, Yu-na?

871
01:10:59,790 --> 01:11:01,580
81GI 0963

872
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:04,750
I've found that car.

873
01:11:10,759 --> 01:11:12,929
Where are you right now? Where?

874
01:11:13,512 --> 01:11:14,762
Don't move. Stay right there.

875
01:12:17,701 --> 01:12:20,251
Why did she follow me all the way here?

876
01:12:29,338 --> 01:12:30,378
Yu-na!

877
01:12:33,633 --> 01:12:35,433
The man in the sketch

878
01:12:35,802 --> 01:12:37,682
and the owner of that car look alike.

879
01:12:39,348 --> 01:12:41,848
Could he be the culprit?

880
01:12:50,400 --> 01:12:51,400
What's the matter?

881
01:12:51,985 --> 01:12:53,445
He looks a lot like...

882
01:12:54,988 --> 01:12:56,278
someone I know.

883
01:13:06,625 --> 01:13:09,375
I'll look into it now. You should go home.

884
01:13:10,003 --> 01:13:11,003
Okay.

885
01:13:45,664 --> 01:13:48,384
I told him to wait,
but he's making me wait.

886
01:13:58,885 --> 01:14:00,005
Anyone here?

887
01:14:15,652 --> 01:14:16,952
Is anybody here?

888
01:15:35,148 --> 01:15:38,858
The dreaded Mago has come
instead of the one I've been waiting for.

889
01:15:39,528 --> 01:15:40,568
Why?

890
01:15:41,738 --> 01:15:44,368
I'm the deity you've been waiting for
the most.

891
01:15:44,616 --> 01:15:45,906
Am I wrong?

892
01:15:48,787 --> 01:15:53,747
You didn't care about reincarnation,
healing, and connections.

893
01:15:55,001 --> 01:15:58,001
You only wished to see me and vanish.

894
01:15:59,422 --> 01:16:02,092
So? Are you here to do that for me?

895
01:16:04,177 --> 01:16:05,887
I've heard the flowers have bloomed.

896
01:16:07,138 --> 01:16:08,638
You finally have

897
01:16:09,391 --> 01:16:11,481
something to lose too.

898
01:16:12,894 --> 01:16:15,734
Do you think
I'm afraid to see the flowers fall?

899
01:16:15,814 --> 01:16:18,024
What about the one
that helped you bloom the flowers?

900
01:16:19,276 --> 01:16:21,606
What if you lose him?

901
01:16:33,164 --> 01:16:34,674
Long time no see, Chan-sung.

902
01:16:46,011 --> 01:16:48,471
Man-wol, you conceited and foolish thing.

903
01:16:49,055 --> 01:16:51,595
Did you say you weren't afraid
to see the flowers fall?

904
01:16:52,267 --> 01:16:53,267
No.

905
01:16:54,394 --> 01:16:56,484
Your flowers will begin to fall

906
01:16:56,563 --> 01:16:58,903
when you become afraid.

907
01:18:22,107 --> 01:18:25,067
<i>So the price Chan-sung needs to pay
in return</i>

908
01:18:25,151 --> 01:18:26,701
won't be fair nor reasonable.

909
01:18:27,696 --> 01:18:30,276
You can stroke my hair in your room

910
01:18:30,365 --> 01:18:31,985
to help me fall asleep.

911
01:18:32,075 --> 01:18:33,735
What's with you? You're too naughty.

912
01:18:33,827 --> 01:18:35,157
You were really scared.

913
01:18:35,912 --> 01:18:38,622
<i>I don't want you to pay the price,</i>

914
01:18:38,707 --> 01:18:41,747
<i>so I'll do everything I can
to clean up after you.</i>

915
01:18:41,835 --> 01:18:43,875
Don't be afraid when you leave me behind.

916
01:18:44,170 --> 01:18:46,670
<i>This is how I, just a weak human,</i>

917
01:18:46,756 --> 01:18:50,136
love you with all my heart.

918
01:18:51,344 --> 01:18:53,354
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

919
01:18:56,963 --> 01:18:59,133
What about the one
that helped you bloom the flowers?

920
01:19:00,716 --> 01:19:03,086
What if you lose him?

921
01:19:06,097 --> 01:19:09,097
Man-wol, you conceited and foolish thing.

922
01:19:09,392 --> 01:19:11,772
Did you say
you aren't afraid to see the flowers fall?

923
01:19:14,397 --> 01:19:15,437
No.

924
01:19:16,566 --> 01:19:18,726
Your flowers will begin to fall

925
01:19:18,818 --> 01:19:21,028
when you become afraid.

926
01:19:31,038 --> 01:19:32,498
Long time no see, Chan-sung.

927
01:19:41,632 --> 01:19:45,142
Are you waiting for me to say,
"Why are you doing this to me?

928
01:19:45,219 --> 01:19:46,509
I'm so scared."

929
01:19:46,595 --> 01:19:48,805
And when I start shivering in fear

930
01:19:48,889 --> 01:19:51,269
and the flowers slowly start to fall,

931
01:19:51,350 --> 01:19:54,600
is that when you'll drag me
to my afterlife?

932
01:19:55,021 --> 01:19:56,111
I'm not surprised.

933
01:19:56,397 --> 01:20:00,147
I already know how cheap you guys can be.

934
01:20:04,071 --> 01:20:05,571
There's no need to wait.

935
01:20:06,365 --> 01:20:08,525
You should just bring him to me

936
01:20:09,243 --> 01:20:10,663
right now.

937
01:20:11,037 --> 01:20:12,707
We can end this once and for all,

938
01:20:13,205 --> 01:20:14,865
and I'll finally vanish.

939
01:20:17,126 --> 01:20:19,496
That's exactly what I've been wishing for

940
01:20:20,588 --> 01:20:22,548
during the endless years I had to endure.

941
01:20:24,717 --> 01:20:25,927
Koo Chan-sung

942
01:20:26,927 --> 01:20:29,137
will eventually bring him to you.

943
01:20:29,221 --> 01:20:31,221
Why do you keep
getting Chan-sung involved?

944
01:20:31,307 --> 01:20:33,477
I'm not the one
who got him involved in this.

945
01:20:35,519 --> 01:20:38,019
It's the one that wants you
to leave in peace.

946
01:20:39,523 --> 01:20:42,533
You've been enduring
for the past 1,000 years,

947
01:20:42,610 --> 01:20:44,400
and all you wish is to cease to exist.

948
01:20:44,487 --> 01:20:47,777
So the price Chan-sung needs to pay
in return

949
01:20:47,865 --> 01:20:50,405
won't be fair nor reasonable.

950
01:20:53,704 --> 01:20:55,254
I tried to stop him.

951
01:20:55,498 --> 01:20:56,958
He chose to stay by my side.

952
01:20:57,458 --> 01:20:59,668
You wicked thing.

953
01:20:59,752 --> 01:21:01,252
Yes, that's right.

954
01:21:01,629 --> 01:21:03,049
I'm a wicked witch who made him stay

955
01:21:03,130 --> 01:21:05,010
even when I knew
what he'd end up going through.

956
01:21:05,091 --> 01:21:07,011
Yes, you're right. You are very wicked.

957
01:21:07,385 --> 01:21:09,045
Because of you,

958
01:21:09,136 --> 01:21:13,056
he even had to encounter the person
that hurt him the most.

959
01:21:24,360 --> 01:21:26,450
What more do you think

960
01:21:26,946 --> 01:21:29,066
he'll have to go through because of you?

961
01:21:36,372 --> 01:21:38,752
You're shaking like a leaf.

962
01:21:39,625 --> 01:21:42,035
It's very amusing to watch.

963
01:22:06,902 --> 01:22:08,152
You're Chan-sung, right?

964
01:22:08,571 --> 01:22:09,821
Don't you remember me?

965
01:22:09,905 --> 01:22:12,445
I'm Seol Ji-won.
We used to study in Boston together.

966
01:22:13,909 --> 01:22:15,159
Yes, Seol Ji-won.

967
01:22:16,287 --> 01:22:17,407
It's you.

968
01:22:18,581 --> 01:22:19,621
What brings you here?

969
01:22:19,707 --> 01:22:21,497
Did Sanchez tell you about me?

970
01:22:21,584 --> 01:22:22,964
Or was it Mi-ra?

971
01:22:25,504 --> 01:22:26,884
No, it was someone else.

972
01:22:27,047 --> 01:22:28,837
She told me she saw you on the street.

973
01:22:28,924 --> 01:22:30,804
But I'm surprised that you're really here.

974
01:22:32,219 --> 01:22:33,349
Oh, really?

975
01:22:43,606 --> 01:22:46,276
I'm sure you didn't come here
because you missed me.

976
01:22:46,358 --> 01:22:47,528
So, what brings you here?

977
01:22:50,404 --> 01:22:52,824
I heard you came back to Korea
to get into law school.

978
01:22:52,907 --> 01:22:54,027
Did you quit studying?

979
01:22:54,116 --> 01:22:57,366
You told me your father was a judge.
Did he give up on you?

980
01:22:58,496 --> 01:23:00,706
He didn't give up on me,
but he did pass away.

981
01:23:00,790 --> 01:23:03,330
So I'm just doing what I like to do now.

982
01:23:03,417 --> 01:23:05,337
And what exactly is that?

983
01:23:12,134 --> 01:23:13,434
It must be wine.

984
01:23:18,974 --> 01:23:20,394
Do you have a lot of good wine?

985
01:23:25,356 --> 01:23:26,566
Can I have a glass?

986
01:23:28,108 --> 01:23:30,488
Okay, sure.

987
01:23:38,494 --> 01:23:39,794
Was it him?

988
01:23:40,871 --> 01:23:42,371
Did he kill you?

989
01:25:05,873 --> 01:25:07,213
What are you doing here?

990
01:25:15,716 --> 01:25:17,176
What about you? What did you do here?

991
01:25:22,264 --> 01:25:23,644
Is what you like to do...

992
01:25:24,934 --> 01:25:26,314
murdering people?

993
01:26:16,402 --> 01:26:18,652
Why won't he pick up his phone?

994
01:26:22,616 --> 01:26:24,326
I need to go back to Chan-sung's place.

995
01:26:24,410 --> 01:26:26,910
You've been there many times already.

996
01:26:27,621 --> 01:26:28,461
He'll come.

997
01:26:28,539 --> 01:26:30,619
He didn't show up or pick up the phone.

998
01:26:30,708 --> 01:26:31,708
This is weird.

999
01:26:33,002 --> 01:26:34,962
I need to know where he is to go find him.

1000
01:26:35,587 --> 01:26:37,127
I'm sure there's a reason.

1001
01:26:37,214 --> 01:26:38,974
Why are you so restless?

1002
01:26:52,146 --> 01:26:54,106
What about the one
that helped you bloom the flowers?

1003
01:26:54,440 --> 01:26:56,980
What if you lose him?

1004
01:26:58,694 --> 01:27:00,614
I heard something ominous.

1005
01:27:06,660 --> 01:27:07,910
I'm going to go find him.

1006
01:27:08,328 --> 01:27:09,408
Ms. Jang.

1007
01:27:14,543 --> 01:27:16,713
Why won't he pick up the phone?

1008
01:27:30,267 --> 01:27:32,387
-Hello?
-What am I going to do?

1009
01:27:33,103 --> 01:27:34,353
What's wrong, Yu-na?

1010
01:27:34,938 --> 01:27:37,438
I think Mr. Koo got hurt.

1011
01:27:38,859 --> 01:27:41,199
What if he died?

1012
01:27:41,820 --> 01:27:42,860
What?

1013
01:27:43,739 --> 01:27:45,529
Mr. Third Choice is dead?

1014
01:27:45,741 --> 01:27:49,241
I think he was killed when he went
to catch the murderer.

1015
01:27:54,083 --> 01:27:56,343
Ms. Jang.

1016
01:27:56,794 --> 01:27:57,804
This is bad.

1017
01:28:00,881 --> 01:28:02,551
Mr. Koo is dead.

1018
01:28:06,470 --> 01:28:07,470
What?

1019
01:28:13,352 --> 01:28:14,902
Yu-na followed some car

1020
01:28:15,604 --> 01:28:18,984
to find the murderer of the guests,

1021
01:28:19,525 --> 01:28:22,435
but Mr. Koo said
it was too dangerous for her

1022
01:28:22,736 --> 01:28:24,236
and went over himself.

1023
01:28:31,245 --> 01:28:32,615
Stop talking nonsense.

1024
01:28:35,207 --> 01:28:36,707
Why would Chan-sung die?

1025
01:28:37,126 --> 01:28:39,626
Yu-na saw him carried into an ambulance.

1026
01:29:29,052 --> 01:29:30,302
Explain the situation.

1027
01:29:31,930 --> 01:29:33,100
What happened?

1028
01:29:36,059 --> 01:29:37,599
Stop crying!

1029
01:29:46,320 --> 01:29:47,400
Mr. Koo?

1030
01:31:21,581 --> 01:31:23,921
Ji Hyeon-jung, you little... Come here.

1031
01:31:24,001 --> 01:31:26,551
-Ms. Jang! Goodness, Ms. Jang!
-You jerk!

1032
01:31:26,628 --> 01:31:27,798
Ms. Jang!

1033
01:31:28,547 --> 01:31:31,757
-You said he--
-My goodness.

1034
01:31:32,134 --> 01:31:35,104
You didn't die. I'm so relieved.

1035
01:31:57,993 --> 01:31:59,123
Goodness.

1036
01:32:02,205 --> 01:32:03,365
You're alive.

1037
01:32:07,461 --> 01:32:09,801
I thought you came as a guest.

1038
01:32:10,047 --> 01:32:12,007
What? A guest...

1039
01:32:18,096 --> 01:32:20,306
You went there to meet the murderer alone.

1040
01:32:20,390 --> 01:32:22,890
We couldn't get a hold of you
and heard someone got badly hurt.

1041
01:32:22,976 --> 01:32:24,766
I thought it was you.

1042
01:32:26,229 --> 01:32:30,029
I knew it could be dangerous.
I didn't go in there without any plan.

1043
01:32:30,400 --> 01:32:32,940
I had already called
a police officer I knew.

1044
01:32:33,820 --> 01:32:34,650
Freeze.

1045
01:32:43,038 --> 01:32:45,578
Great job. Then who got hurt?

1046
01:32:46,541 --> 01:32:47,791
The culprit.

1047
01:32:48,960 --> 01:32:52,960
Seol Ji-won,
you are under arrest for murder.

1048
01:33:05,060 --> 01:33:06,100
Put that down.

1049
01:33:23,203 --> 01:33:26,833
He's not in critical condition now,
so he will live to pay for what he did.

1050
01:33:26,998 --> 01:33:28,958
Gosh, I'm so relieved.

1051
01:33:29,042 --> 01:33:31,462
I was really shocked
because I thought you came as a guest.

1052
01:33:31,545 --> 01:33:33,415
I knew he wasn't a guest
as soon as I saw him.

1053
01:33:33,505 --> 01:33:35,715
No, you didn't. You cried.

1054
01:33:35,799 --> 01:33:37,469
I saw you wiping your tears.

1055
01:33:37,551 --> 01:33:39,141
I had a runny nose.

1056
01:33:39,219 --> 01:33:41,969
Ms. Choe, I saw your legs shaking.

1057
01:33:45,600 --> 01:33:47,770
I'm sorry that I made everyone worried.

1058
01:33:47,853 --> 01:33:50,733
And thank you for worrying about me.

1059
01:33:50,814 --> 01:33:53,574
Our dead hearts skipped a beat
thanks to you.

1060
01:33:53,650 --> 01:33:55,240
That was thrilling.

1061
01:33:55,318 --> 01:33:58,108
Ms. Jang will begin
to throw a huge fit soon,

1062
01:33:58,196 --> 01:33:59,656
so let's survive that too.

1063
01:33:59,739 --> 01:34:00,739
Okay.

1064
01:34:08,665 --> 01:34:09,745
-We can do it!
-We can do it!

1065
01:34:13,795 --> 01:34:14,955
Jang Man-wol.

1066
01:34:19,384 --> 01:34:20,514
Where did she go?

1067
01:34:23,138 --> 01:34:26,598
I brought an extra one because I knew
a few bottles wouldn't cut it.

1068
01:34:31,146 --> 01:34:33,606
Jang Man-wol, where have you been?

1069
01:34:35,525 --> 01:34:36,735
Did you go shopping?

1070
01:34:36,818 --> 01:34:38,198
Chan-sung, sit down.

1071
01:34:48,955 --> 01:34:50,365
Did you go to the pharmacy?

1072
01:34:50,457 --> 01:34:54,537
Yes, we don't have anything
that can treat the living.

1073
01:34:55,170 --> 01:34:56,630
Did you clean the entire pharmacy out?

1074
01:34:56,713 --> 01:34:58,473
Just sit down, will you?

1075
01:34:58,882 --> 01:34:59,972
Let me see.

1076
01:35:08,475 --> 01:35:10,135
You're all wounded.

1077
01:35:14,231 --> 01:35:16,361
What do I have to put on you?

1078
01:35:17,234 --> 01:35:18,904
Let's put on the most expensive one.

1079
01:35:28,495 --> 01:35:30,115
-That stings.
-It hurts?

1080
01:35:31,081 --> 01:35:32,961
Darn it. I guess
this ointment isn't a good one.

1081
01:35:33,375 --> 01:35:34,375
Let me see.

1082
01:35:38,421 --> 01:35:40,591
Wait, this is the ointment
for hemorrhoids.

1083
01:35:40,674 --> 01:35:41,684
What?

1084
01:35:43,426 --> 01:35:46,346
Sorry. I applied the ointment
for buttholes on your face.

1085
01:35:48,306 --> 01:35:49,306
Come here.

1086
01:35:49,474 --> 01:35:50,774
No, that's okay.

1087
01:35:51,309 --> 01:35:53,729
If this heals buttholes,
I'm sure it'll heal my face too.

1088
01:35:53,812 --> 01:35:55,562
Buttholes and faces aren't the same.

1089
01:35:55,981 --> 01:35:57,611
Give it back. I'll apply another one.

1090
01:36:02,028 --> 01:36:03,358
Were you scared

1091
01:36:03,738 --> 01:36:05,868
that I died
and came to the hotel as a guest?

1092
01:36:11,121 --> 01:36:13,791
How could you of all people
be confused and scared?

1093
01:36:18,670 --> 01:36:20,210
Because I was afraid.

1094
01:36:24,050 --> 01:36:26,050
Just like the world turned pitch-dark,

1095
01:36:28,138 --> 01:36:29,558
I was scared.

1096
01:36:36,396 --> 01:36:39,766
No matter how desperately I wanted money,
I never made that kind of mistake.

1097
01:36:40,692 --> 01:36:42,362
You made me look like a fool.

1098
01:36:43,111 --> 01:36:45,071
All of my employees were watching too.

1099
01:36:45,572 --> 01:36:47,122
Gosh, this is embarrassing.

1100
01:36:49,618 --> 01:36:51,658
What is this? Darn it.

1101
01:36:53,455 --> 01:36:54,455
Wait here.

1102
01:36:54,873 --> 01:36:57,833
I'll go look for a guest
who was a pharmacist.

1103
01:37:01,379 --> 01:37:03,049
You seem pretty shook up yourself.

1104
01:37:03,131 --> 01:37:04,721
Shouldn't you take some medicine?

1105
01:37:05,508 --> 01:37:07,888
Why? Do you have any pills for that?

1106
01:37:18,647 --> 01:37:20,067
You were really scared.

1107
01:37:28,281 --> 01:37:29,701
Are you a pharmacist or what?

1108
01:37:32,410 --> 01:37:34,410
I'm supposed to take care of you.

1109
01:37:54,599 --> 01:37:56,769
Your flowers will begin to fall

1110
01:37:56,976 --> 01:37:59,056
when you become afraid.

1111
01:38:08,405 --> 01:38:09,735
I have good news too.

1112
01:38:11,574 --> 01:38:12,914
Your Yeon-u...

1113
01:38:12,992 --> 01:38:15,872
Right. Detective Park Yeong-su
caught the culprit.

1114
01:38:15,954 --> 01:38:17,544
He'll probably get promoted.

1115
01:38:26,548 --> 01:38:29,718
I found all the drugs and syringes
he used to kill the victims.

1116
01:38:31,094 --> 01:38:33,894
I think he illegally smuggled in
the drugs while importing wine.

1117
01:38:34,264 --> 01:38:36,354
It's the symbol of
the website Helllo, right?

1118
01:38:36,433 --> 01:38:38,443
Did you find Seol Ji-won in the website?

1119
01:38:39,185 --> 01:38:40,225
Actually,

1120
01:38:41,604 --> 01:38:43,274
I received a tip.

1121
01:38:46,401 --> 01:38:47,531
Who?

1122
01:38:48,361 --> 01:38:50,111
You're the dead woman, Lee Do-yeon?

1123
01:38:50,363 --> 01:38:52,123
My husband isn't the culprit.

1124
01:38:52,198 --> 01:38:53,828
The murderer is right here.

1125
01:38:53,908 --> 01:38:55,698
You shouldn't make a prank call.

1126
01:38:55,827 --> 01:38:58,157
Blood. There's blood.

1127
01:38:58,621 --> 01:39:00,791
He collected samples of blood
from his victims.

1128
01:39:00,874 --> 01:39:02,924
Please come here. It's dangerous here.

1129
01:39:03,543 --> 01:39:06,053
The lead that there were traces
that the victims' blood was drawn

1130
01:39:06,129 --> 01:39:07,919
was never disclosed to the public.

1131
01:39:09,048 --> 01:39:10,928
I came here because that bothered me.

1132
01:39:12,260 --> 01:39:14,010
I really found their blood here.

1133
01:39:14,512 --> 01:39:16,472
He's really like a demon.

1134
01:39:17,474 --> 01:39:20,354
He displayed the victims' blood
among his wine bottles.

1135
01:39:20,810 --> 01:39:22,730
But who do you think gave me that call?

1136
01:39:22,812 --> 01:39:25,272
There's no way a dead woman
could have called me.

1137
01:39:28,151 --> 01:39:29,651
That's really strange.

1138
01:39:35,158 --> 01:39:38,368
You can't let a ghost
take over your body like that.

1139
01:39:39,579 --> 01:39:43,419
Promise me. Don't you ever do
something like that without me.

1140
01:39:43,625 --> 01:39:46,915
The ghost just helped me call it in
and gather evidence.

1141
01:39:48,630 --> 01:39:49,920
Take them with you.

1142
01:39:50,507 --> 01:39:52,047
And go home and rest for the day.

1143
01:39:54,052 --> 01:39:56,012
Now I have a lot to take home.

1144
01:39:57,472 --> 01:39:59,562
-What's this?
-A massager.

1145
01:40:00,225 --> 01:40:03,305
Put it on your neck
before going to sleep. It'll be nice.

1146
01:40:03,394 --> 01:40:06,564
There are an sleep mask
and a bottle of champagne.

1147
01:40:06,648 --> 01:40:09,688
Right. Caviar. This is really expensive,
just so you know.

1148
01:40:09,776 --> 01:40:10,936
Take your time with it.

1149
01:40:11,027 --> 01:40:13,317
You gave me things
that are very valuable to you.

1150
01:40:15,865 --> 01:40:17,825
Take one of my cars
since you have a lot...

1151
01:40:19,828 --> 01:40:20,828
Forget it.

1152
01:40:21,621 --> 01:40:23,371
You should just keep driving one.

1153
01:40:24,165 --> 01:40:25,165
Really?

1154
01:40:25,458 --> 01:40:28,338
The red one. Can I take the red one?

1155
01:40:28,419 --> 01:40:29,379
What?

1156
01:40:31,256 --> 01:40:35,426
Why? Do you like the color red?
You don't like it.

1157
01:40:35,510 --> 01:40:36,640
I do.

1158
01:40:37,428 --> 01:40:38,298
Is that so?

1159
01:40:39,264 --> 01:40:40,354
Really?

1160
01:40:42,475 --> 01:40:43,685
Sure.

1161
01:40:44,435 --> 01:40:47,225
There's only one red car,

1162
01:40:47,981 --> 01:40:49,361
but you can drive it.

1163
01:40:52,110 --> 01:40:53,280
You can keep it.

1164
01:40:54,612 --> 01:40:55,612
Thank you.

1165
01:40:59,617 --> 01:41:01,157
This isn't the right key.

1166
01:41:01,703 --> 01:41:03,123
It's that one. Over there.

1167
01:41:10,420 --> 01:41:11,420
Here.

1168
01:41:12,171 --> 01:41:14,091
It's nice to have a near-death experience.

1169
01:41:15,174 --> 01:41:16,384
I'll just drive this one.

1170
01:41:16,634 --> 01:41:17,644
Are you kidding me?

1171
01:41:17,844 --> 01:41:18,854
I was testing you.

1172
01:41:18,928 --> 01:41:21,508
The red car versus me. I won.

1173
01:41:21,598 --> 01:41:24,018
You would've lost
if it was a new poop colored car.

1174
01:41:24,100 --> 01:41:26,100
I know that your favorite is the red one.

1175
01:41:26,185 --> 01:41:28,095
I beat the red car.
It means I beat them all.

1176
01:41:29,188 --> 01:41:32,438
I had no idea you were such a sly snake.

1177
01:41:35,236 --> 01:41:38,156
I think I need to go
to the police station a few times.

1178
01:41:38,448 --> 01:41:41,578
To explain what happened
without involving the ghost,

1179
01:41:41,659 --> 01:41:43,999
I really have to be a sly snake this time.

1180
01:41:44,120 --> 01:41:46,460
Anyway, Yeon-u must be flustered.

1181
01:41:47,290 --> 01:41:49,880
He received two tips from ghosts.

1182
01:41:51,377 --> 01:41:53,167
He may have a fine figure,

1183
01:41:53,546 --> 01:41:56,796
but he got scared easily
and found ghosts really scary.

1184
01:41:57,133 --> 01:41:58,433
Yeon-u did?

1185
01:41:59,552 --> 01:42:01,552
You must've grown up with him
since you were young.

1186
01:42:02,388 --> 01:42:04,638
Yeon-u's mother raised me.

1187
01:42:07,143 --> 01:42:09,103
When I was very young,

1188
01:42:10,396 --> 01:42:12,606
I was dying in the wilds.

1189
01:42:13,358 --> 01:42:15,528
A merchant who was passing by
saved me, apparently.

1190
01:42:16,778 --> 01:42:18,698
And Yeon-u's mom was the one
who took me in.

1191
01:42:21,616 --> 01:42:24,236
But she passed away not long after.

1192
01:42:24,827 --> 01:42:29,207
Yeon-u and I were
practically brother and sister.

1193
01:42:29,332 --> 01:42:30,672
That's how we lived.

1194
01:42:33,836 --> 01:42:38,586
He was dexterous,
so he'd make clothes for me too.

1195
01:42:44,555 --> 01:42:48,425
I think he's living
a good life as a cop now.

1196
01:42:52,355 --> 01:42:55,015
I don't think
I've told you about my past before.

1197
01:42:55,858 --> 01:42:56,978
You haven't.

1198
01:43:01,364 --> 01:43:04,084
-Perhaps, the flowers are the reason.
-Maybe it's time for them to fall.

1199
01:43:31,227 --> 01:43:32,647
I should go.

1200
01:43:37,442 --> 01:43:38,442
Hey.

1201
01:43:58,337 --> 01:44:00,297
Maybe it's time for them to fall.

1202
01:44:20,443 --> 01:44:22,863
I hope you keep it up
and take good care of me

1203
01:44:23,404 --> 01:44:24,704
and then...

1204
01:44:25,865 --> 01:44:27,025
see me off.

1205
01:44:27,825 --> 01:44:29,195
That's what Mago wants.

1206
01:44:30,203 --> 01:44:32,663
You must be doing a good job.

1207
01:44:32,789 --> 01:44:35,329
I think the flower will bloom.

1208
01:44:36,042 --> 01:44:38,382
You should look after it well

1209
01:44:38,920 --> 01:44:41,380
so you can send her off.

1210
01:44:41,839 --> 01:44:45,799
Who is the last guest
you'll be sending off?

1211
01:44:46,552 --> 01:44:48,852
I'll become your last customer.

1212
01:44:49,722 --> 01:44:51,272
When you see me off,

1213
01:44:53,643 --> 01:44:55,103
don't feel lonely.

1214
01:45:30,429 --> 01:45:31,719
When will he wake up?

1215
01:45:31,805 --> 01:45:33,765
Probably in a couple of hours.

1216
01:45:55,579 --> 01:45:58,749
-Did he wake up?
-He will in a few hours.

1217
01:46:03,212 --> 01:46:05,172
-Where did he go?
-He was here a second ago.

1218
01:46:05,255 --> 01:46:06,585
Don't just stand there. Find him!

1219
01:46:06,673 --> 01:46:07,763
I'm sorry, sir!

1220
01:46:32,032 --> 01:46:33,452
Is what you like to do...

1221
01:46:34,493 --> 01:46:35,663
murdering people?

1222
01:46:37,496 --> 01:46:38,746
What are you talking about?

1223
01:46:39,164 --> 01:46:40,374
You killed...

1224
01:46:41,333 --> 01:46:42,463
a person.

1225
01:46:44,878 --> 01:46:45,798
Says who?

1226
01:46:45,879 --> 01:46:47,209
The person you killed...

1227
01:46:48,048 --> 01:46:49,378
is here with us.

1228
01:46:52,136 --> 01:46:53,886
You're insane.

1229
01:46:54,388 --> 01:46:57,978
Do you think it's over once people die?

1230
01:47:03,355 --> 01:47:04,815
Our souls remain.

1231
01:47:07,651 --> 01:47:10,571
Your seventh victim is here
with us at the moment.

1232
01:47:14,450 --> 01:47:15,490
And this is...

1233
01:47:18,120 --> 01:47:19,540
her blood.

1234
01:47:26,795 --> 01:47:29,005
Must I find the other six for you
to believe me?

1235
01:47:55,741 --> 01:47:58,541
-Who are you?
-I didn't find them.

1236
01:47:58,619 --> 01:48:00,039
Your victim did.

1237
01:48:00,120 --> 01:48:02,580
Don't lie to me. That's impossible.

1238
01:48:02,664 --> 01:48:04,254
You may not know this,

1239
01:48:05,083 --> 01:48:06,883
but she's been next to you
this whole time.

1240
01:48:16,678 --> 01:48:19,098
She's also telling me what you are hiding

1241
01:48:19,890 --> 01:48:21,140
behind you.

1242
01:48:45,040 --> 01:48:46,830
So, ghosts exist?

1243
01:48:52,965 --> 01:48:54,255
Will you be here soon?

1244
01:48:55,133 --> 01:48:56,343
What time?

1245
01:48:57,636 --> 01:48:59,006
That's too late.

1246
01:49:16,613 --> 01:49:18,033
DETECTIVE PARK YEONG-SU

1247
01:49:20,617 --> 01:49:21,697
Yes, Detective.

1248
01:49:22,035 --> 01:49:25,325
Mr. Koo, we need you here
at the hospital now.

1249
01:49:56,737 --> 01:49:57,907
You're here.

1250
01:49:57,988 --> 01:49:59,108
As I said on the phone,

1251
01:49:59,197 --> 01:50:01,197
Seol Ji-won will only talk to you.

1252
01:50:01,283 --> 01:50:02,583
Would that be all right?

1253
01:50:04,995 --> 01:50:05,995
Yes.

1254
01:50:38,487 --> 01:50:39,567
You're here.

1255
01:50:44,076 --> 01:50:46,116
Look at where I am thanks to you.

1256
01:50:46,870 --> 01:50:48,330
No, this is on you.

1257
01:50:49,915 --> 01:50:53,415
What brought you here is
the victim you killed.

1258
01:50:57,089 --> 01:50:58,719
You said ghosts existed.

1259
01:51:00,384 --> 01:51:02,474
Is someone aiding you right now as well?

1260
01:51:03,971 --> 01:51:07,721
Yes, I have someone protecting me
even at this moment.

1261
01:51:15,148 --> 01:51:16,268
Is this the guy?

1262
01:51:18,819 --> 01:51:20,569
Should I just push him?

1263
01:51:21,363 --> 01:51:22,363
No, don't.

1264
01:51:22,864 --> 01:51:25,624
He must live and suffer,
paying for what he's done.

1265
01:51:25,909 --> 01:51:26,829
Sure.

1266
01:51:26,910 --> 01:51:30,460
I don't want to go through the trouble
because of some scumbag anyway.

1267
01:51:30,539 --> 01:51:32,169
-Of course.
-Hey!

1268
01:51:34,042 --> 01:51:35,252
What are you doing?

1269
01:51:35,919 --> 01:51:38,339
I was talking to my guardian about you.

1270
01:51:42,843 --> 01:51:44,723
Damn you, Chan-sung.

1271
01:51:44,803 --> 01:51:47,813
My life started to fall apart
because of you, you know.

1272
01:51:47,889 --> 01:51:50,679
No, it was because of what you had done.

1273
01:52:02,904 --> 01:52:03,864
Cute.

1274
01:52:07,242 --> 01:52:09,122
Do you have proof that I sent it?

1275
01:52:09,619 --> 01:52:12,159
Also, who will believe you?

1276
01:52:12,998 --> 01:52:16,248
You think you're something
just because you're smart, don't you?

1277
01:52:16,918 --> 01:52:18,128
You're so full of yourself.

1278
01:52:26,386 --> 01:52:28,216
No one has to believe me

1279
01:52:28,513 --> 01:52:30,223
except for one person.

1280
01:52:32,434 --> 01:52:35,524
The man who knew his youngest son so well

1281
01:52:35,896 --> 01:52:38,106
that he sent the son abroad.

1282
01:52:39,566 --> 01:52:41,106
I'm talking about your father, a judge.

1283
01:52:50,827 --> 01:52:52,537
How about we have a little bet?

1284
01:52:53,997 --> 01:52:56,877
Between his son who isn't reliable at all

1285
01:52:57,417 --> 01:53:01,127
and a straight-A student
of a prestigious US university,

1286
01:53:01,213 --> 01:53:03,133
who will your father believe?

1287
01:53:31,743 --> 01:53:34,503
Before I tell your father
about everything,

1288
01:53:34,579 --> 01:53:36,159
get lost.

1289
01:53:40,919 --> 01:53:43,209
I should've just pulled
the trigger back then.

1290
01:53:53,014 --> 01:53:54,064
Do you

1291
01:53:55,392 --> 01:53:56,982
know him personally?

1292
01:53:58,854 --> 01:54:00,484
Our ill-fated relationship goes way back.

1293
01:54:01,606 --> 01:54:03,106
I thought it had been severed,

1294
01:54:03,733 --> 01:54:05,073
but we met again.

1295
01:54:06,695 --> 01:54:08,565
Because of you,

1296
01:54:08,738 --> 01:54:12,278
he even had to encounter the person
that hurt him the most.

1297
01:54:12,576 --> 01:54:14,656
What more do you think

1298
01:54:15,203 --> 01:54:17,503
he'll have to go through because of you?

1299
01:54:22,127 --> 01:54:23,377
What you've done

1300
01:54:23,920 --> 01:54:25,340
won't end with your death.

1301
01:54:25,422 --> 01:54:27,592
The only way to save your soul is

1302
01:54:27,924 --> 01:54:30,514
to stay alive and pay for your sins.

1303
01:54:30,594 --> 01:54:32,014
How are they my sins?

1304
01:54:32,095 --> 01:54:34,845
I just did what other people
asked me to do.

1305
01:54:37,517 --> 01:54:40,267
Do you have any idea
how enthusiastic people become

1306
01:54:40,353 --> 01:54:42,693
when it comes to hating
and cursing others?

1307
01:54:43,273 --> 01:54:46,233
Soccer players score goals
because that's what people want.

1308
01:54:46,318 --> 01:54:48,358
And I killed those people

1309
01:54:48,445 --> 01:54:51,315
because that was what people wanted,
so how is that my responsibility?

1310
01:54:51,406 --> 01:54:54,026
That's probably where people go
to express their filthy emotions.

1311
01:54:54,409 --> 01:54:58,209
But no one actually wants someone
to put their filthy thoughts into action.

1312
01:54:58,288 --> 01:54:59,828
Get down here, Ji-won!

1313
01:55:05,754 --> 01:55:07,674
I uploaded a post
to express my hatred for you.

1314
01:55:10,217 --> 01:55:12,137
I hope it receives a lot of support.

1315
01:56:55,780 --> 01:56:57,660
I guess you're able to see me now.

1316
01:56:58,658 --> 01:56:59,738
He was right.

1317
01:57:01,036 --> 01:57:02,696
Death really isn't the end.

1318
01:57:03,288 --> 01:57:04,288
Yes.

1319
01:57:05,290 --> 01:57:06,790
You're a ghost now.

1320
01:57:12,339 --> 01:57:14,969
Chan-sung probably didn't want this
to happen,

1321
01:57:15,675 --> 01:57:18,345
but I couldn't wait for you
to fall down the building and die.

1322
01:57:19,721 --> 01:57:23,101
I'm not allowed to harm
a living human being.

1323
01:57:23,516 --> 01:57:25,346
But it's a vengeful ghost like you,

1324
01:57:26,353 --> 01:57:27,903
that's not the case.

1325
01:57:29,814 --> 01:57:31,234
"A vengeful ghost"?

1326
01:57:39,282 --> 01:57:41,412
You deserve to be thrown
in a garbage truck.

1327
01:57:42,619 --> 01:57:44,579
I'll destroy you and turn you to ashes.

1328
01:57:45,080 --> 01:57:47,830
I hope you turn into trash
and head to your afterlife.

1329
01:58:07,185 --> 01:58:08,345
What was that?

1330
01:58:09,229 --> 01:58:11,189
What's protecting you?

1331
01:58:13,316 --> 01:58:15,066
It must be my resentment.

1332
01:58:15,402 --> 01:58:19,452
My hatred and curse are
making people go wild.

1333
01:58:23,701 --> 01:58:25,911
I will sacrifice my life

1334
01:58:26,329 --> 01:58:30,999
to curse Koo Chan-sung,
the guy who ruined my life.

1335
01:58:32,127 --> 01:58:33,997
COMPLETE

1336
01:58:34,087 --> 01:58:35,587
YOUR POST HAS BEEN UPLOADED

1337
01:58:40,760 --> 01:58:42,890
I HOPE HE DIES

1338
01:58:42,971 --> 01:58:45,011
I CURSE HIM TOO

1339
01:58:47,308 --> 01:58:50,308
These people's ugly thoughts and emotions

1340
01:58:50,854 --> 01:58:53,154
must've given you
a hideous type of strength.

1341
01:58:53,690 --> 01:58:56,150
Who are you to protect Chan-sung?

1342
01:58:56,276 --> 01:58:58,106
Shut it, you piece of trash.

1343
01:58:58,903 --> 01:59:00,033
You stink.

1344
01:59:01,698 --> 01:59:05,028
I'll get rid of this hideous power
that's protecting you now

1345
01:59:05,118 --> 01:59:07,118
and rip you into pieces.

1346
01:59:08,371 --> 01:59:09,621
You just wait.

1347
01:59:11,749 --> 01:59:14,209
I'm going to become
even uglier and more powerful.

1348
01:59:39,777 --> 01:59:43,277
I requested the Helllo website to delete
the posts that Seol Ji-won uploaded.

1349
01:59:43,573 --> 01:59:47,583
But we couldn't do anything about the ones
that already went viral on the web.

1350
01:59:48,244 --> 01:59:49,164
I'm sorry.

1351
01:59:49,245 --> 01:59:51,075
There's no need for you to apologize.

1352
01:59:51,956 --> 01:59:54,206
Is it okay if I go now?

1353
01:59:54,626 --> 01:59:55,456
Sure.

1354
01:59:58,087 --> 01:59:59,167
Oh, wait.

1355
02:00:00,965 --> 02:00:02,755
When you were at the wine bar,

1356
02:00:03,384 --> 02:00:05,394
were you with a woman by any chance?

1357
02:00:06,971 --> 02:00:08,101
The thing is,

1358
02:00:08,973 --> 02:00:11,433
I got a call from the wine bar.

1359
02:00:11,518 --> 02:00:15,478
And the woman who called told me
that she was the late Lee Do-yeon.

1360
02:00:16,773 --> 02:00:19,233
I know it doesn't make sense,
but I was just wondering--

1361
02:00:19,317 --> 02:00:20,607
It could've been her.

1362
02:00:22,862 --> 02:00:25,282
I believe that souls exist.

1363
02:00:25,532 --> 02:00:27,372
I also believe in reincarnation.

1364
02:00:28,076 --> 02:00:30,446
Oh, reincarnation? I see.

1365
02:00:33,248 --> 02:00:34,788
You draw very well.

1366
02:00:36,125 --> 02:00:37,665
You must be quite dexterous.

1367
02:00:38,419 --> 02:00:39,459
Thank you.

1368
02:00:41,422 --> 02:00:42,422
Okay, then.

1369
02:00:58,731 --> 02:01:00,231
Seol Ji-won

1370
02:01:01,234 --> 02:01:02,324
died.

1371
02:01:02,569 --> 02:01:03,569
I know.

1372
02:01:04,028 --> 02:01:05,358
I met him as a ghost.

1373
02:01:08,783 --> 02:01:11,873
He has become a vengeful ghost,
and he holds resentment toward you.

1374
02:01:12,745 --> 02:01:15,915
Yes, I know. I read the post he uploaded.

1375
02:01:16,749 --> 02:01:19,539
I'm quite shocked
at how much support he got.

1376
02:01:22,505 --> 02:01:23,795
Darn it.

1377
02:01:24,215 --> 02:01:27,045
I should've turned him to ashes
the moment he died.

1378
02:01:27,677 --> 02:01:30,007
I should've brought a gun
instead of a folding fan.

1379
02:01:30,722 --> 02:01:32,472
Was he strong enough to escape from you?

1380
02:01:32,557 --> 02:01:34,597
I want to act like it's not a big deal,

1381
02:01:35,351 --> 02:01:36,601
but it is a big deal.

1382
02:01:38,938 --> 02:01:40,018
Chan-sung.

1383
02:01:40,773 --> 02:01:42,943
Don't go home until we catch him.

1384
02:01:43,026 --> 02:01:44,736
Stay right by my side.

1385
02:01:55,163 --> 02:01:58,083
Do you think Ms. Jang will ban me
from coming to this hotel?

1386
02:01:58,166 --> 02:02:00,286
She probably forgot about it already.

1387
02:02:00,752 --> 02:02:03,382
Mr. Koo turned out to be okay,
so everything will be fine.

1388
02:02:03,463 --> 02:02:05,053
-Really?
-Of course.

1389
02:02:05,131 --> 02:02:07,051
But thanks to you, our hotel guests

1390
02:02:07,133 --> 02:02:09,593
were able to reveal their wrongful deaths.

1391
02:02:10,094 --> 02:02:11,804
Good job, Yu-na.

1392
02:02:13,097 --> 02:02:14,927
Gosh, what a relief.

1393
02:02:16,559 --> 02:02:20,479
We got a new guest last night,
and she asked if she could meet you.

1394
02:02:21,064 --> 02:02:22,074
What?

1395
02:02:33,785 --> 02:02:35,905
You're that woman.

1396
02:02:40,124 --> 02:02:43,254
Thank you for following me
until the very end.

1397
02:02:53,054 --> 02:02:55,774
THE LATE JEONG SU-JEONG

1398
02:03:00,019 --> 02:03:02,309
This is where I actually am.

1399
02:03:02,563 --> 02:03:04,903
But I was too scared to come here.
This is my first time.

1400
02:03:05,650 --> 02:03:07,610
I got murdered as well.

1401
02:03:08,778 --> 02:03:10,488
And I feel like I consoled myself

1402
02:03:12,156 --> 02:03:14,486
by helping out with the murder case.

1403
02:03:21,374 --> 02:03:23,794
I secretly brought it
from the hotel garden.

1404
02:03:24,127 --> 02:03:25,337
Let's put this inside.

1405
02:03:27,463 --> 02:03:29,593
-Hyeon-jung.
-Yes?

1406
02:03:29,966 --> 02:03:33,426
Where are you buried?

1407
02:03:33,636 --> 02:03:35,756
Somewhere in the mountain.

1408
02:03:37,515 --> 02:03:38,805
I don't have a grave.

1409
02:03:42,895 --> 02:03:44,515
Then let's share this space together.

1410
02:03:55,908 --> 02:03:56,868
That's me.

1411
02:03:57,827 --> 02:04:00,867
I was just practicing drawing portraits.

1412
02:04:10,506 --> 02:04:13,926
This is our grave now.

1413
02:04:14,719 --> 02:04:15,969
Do you like it?

1414
02:04:16,888 --> 02:04:18,178
Don't you like it?

1415
02:04:19,724 --> 02:04:21,934
Well, then. Just forget it.

1416
02:04:22,602 --> 02:04:25,692
I already told you that I liked you,
but you ignored it.

1417
02:04:25,897 --> 02:04:27,477
I didn't ignore it.

1418
02:04:30,151 --> 02:04:31,191
Yu-na.

1419
02:04:31,777 --> 02:04:33,527
Your boyfriend

1420
02:04:34,572 --> 02:04:35,822
should be someone kind

1421
02:04:37,492 --> 02:04:39,742
and alive.

1422
02:04:40,119 --> 02:04:41,249
That's why...

1423
02:04:53,174 --> 02:04:54,264
I like you.

1424
02:04:56,385 --> 02:04:58,345
Can't you just like me too--

1425
02:05:25,581 --> 02:05:26,671
Chan-sung.

1426
02:05:28,918 --> 02:05:30,128
Wake up.

1427
02:05:55,152 --> 02:05:57,322
Why are you sleeping
in this uncomfortable couch?

1428
02:05:58,197 --> 02:06:00,447
The only rooms
I can sleep in at this hotel

1429
02:06:00,533 --> 02:06:02,583
is Room 404 and yours.

1430
02:06:03,244 --> 02:06:05,334
If I end up in Incheon
after sleeping in Room 404,

1431
02:06:05,413 --> 02:06:06,753
I'll have a hard time coming to work.

1432
02:06:06,831 --> 02:06:08,291
Who told you to sleep in Room 404?

1433
02:06:08,374 --> 02:06:09,754
I told you to sleep in my room.

1434
02:06:10,251 --> 02:06:12,091
You'll fall asleep in no time

1435
02:06:12,169 --> 02:06:14,459
with the massager and sleep mask.

1436
02:06:14,547 --> 02:06:17,167
Do you think I'll be able to fall asleep
in your room

1437
02:06:17,633 --> 02:06:19,053
even if I had that massager?

1438
02:06:21,554 --> 02:06:25,434
You're right.
After all, you are very healthy.

1439
02:06:27,602 --> 02:06:31,192
Gosh, humans need to sleep well.

1440
02:06:31,731 --> 02:06:32,821
Too bad for you.

1441
02:06:35,067 --> 02:06:36,067
Let's go, then.

1442
02:06:36,736 --> 02:06:39,026
Let me sleep comfortably in your room.

1443
02:06:39,447 --> 02:06:42,197
I don't need that massager.
I'd rather have your arm.

1444
02:06:42,700 --> 02:06:44,740
If you let me use your arm as a pillow,

1445
02:06:45,202 --> 02:06:46,582
I don't need that sleep mask.

1446
02:06:46,912 --> 02:06:48,462
You can stroke my hair

1447
02:06:49,332 --> 02:06:50,462
to help me

1448
02:06:51,292 --> 02:06:52,292
fall asleep.

1449
02:06:53,419 --> 02:06:54,919
What's with you? You're too naughty.

1450
02:06:57,673 --> 02:06:58,923
Cool it down.

1451
02:07:13,648 --> 02:07:16,358
You cool it down. You're blushing.

1452
02:07:19,320 --> 02:07:21,660
I feel so stiff.
Maybe I should try the massager.

1453
02:07:23,908 --> 02:07:24,948
Gosh.

1454
02:07:25,618 --> 02:07:28,618
I am not blushing...

1455
02:07:29,955 --> 02:07:31,075
Chan-sung.

1456
02:07:31,707 --> 02:07:34,207
Forget the massager.
Let's go get acupuncture.

1457
02:07:34,794 --> 02:07:36,134
-What?
-Let's get acupuncture

1458
02:07:36,212 --> 02:07:37,802
and cupping therapy to let some blood out.

1459
02:07:37,880 --> 02:07:39,300
I know a good oriental clinic.

1460
02:07:39,924 --> 02:07:43,974
There's a famous doctor
who can even bring a dead person back.

1461
02:07:46,430 --> 02:07:48,350
You did a great job, ma'am!

1462
02:07:48,432 --> 02:07:49,642
HYOSAENG ORIENTAL CLINIC

1463
02:07:49,725 --> 02:07:51,475
Be sure to come in daily
to get acupuncture.

1464
02:07:51,560 --> 02:07:53,980
Doctor, your herbal medicine
is too expensive.

1465
02:07:54,063 --> 02:07:57,193
It's only because it's really effective.

1466
02:07:57,274 --> 02:07:59,824
And I even gave you
some free samples as well!

1467
02:07:59,902 --> 02:08:00,902
Thank you.

1468
02:08:01,570 --> 02:08:05,320
You mean that doctor
brought back a dead person?

1469
02:08:05,741 --> 02:08:08,871
He's keeping someone who should have died
three years ago alive.

1470
02:08:10,079 --> 02:08:11,499
He must be an amazing doctor.

1471
02:08:11,580 --> 02:08:13,000
Take care, ma'am.

1472
02:08:15,042 --> 02:08:16,542
Is he a reincarnation of Hua Tuo?

1473
02:08:16,627 --> 02:08:17,837
I don't know.

1474
02:08:17,920 --> 02:08:19,510
Ma'am, don't hesitate.

1475
02:08:19,588 --> 02:08:21,548
Buy them for your family members.

1476
02:08:21,632 --> 02:08:24,552
I'll give you ten percent off.

1477
02:08:24,635 --> 02:08:25,635
I'll need to think about it.

1478
02:08:25,720 --> 02:08:27,430
All right, ma'am.

1479
02:08:27,513 --> 02:08:28,813
Take care.

1480
02:08:29,682 --> 02:08:32,602
Keep recommending it to her.

1481
02:08:32,685 --> 02:08:34,055
He seems

1482
02:08:34,812 --> 02:08:37,822
a bit greedy, though, like someone I know.

1483
02:08:41,193 --> 02:08:42,403
You have a guest, honey.

1484
02:08:42,486 --> 02:08:44,026
Thank you for coming.

1485
02:08:44,113 --> 02:08:45,493
Please follow me.

1486
02:08:46,449 --> 02:08:49,029
You don't look too good.

1487
02:08:49,118 --> 02:08:50,488
She must be his wife.

1488
02:08:50,870 --> 02:08:51,910
They look alike.

1489
02:08:51,996 --> 02:08:55,786
Anyway, we have to take the patient
he's been keeping alive

1490
02:08:55,875 --> 02:08:56,955
to our hotel.

1491
02:08:57,042 --> 02:08:59,092
But, isn't the patient still alive?

1492
02:08:59,170 --> 02:09:00,920
How are we supposed
to take them as a guest?

1493
02:09:01,839 --> 02:09:03,219
By killing, of course.

1494
02:09:03,632 --> 02:09:05,972
The Grim Reaper told me
to make sure to kill the patient.

1495
02:09:06,844 --> 02:09:09,724
You even run errands for the Grim Reaper?

1496
02:09:10,723 --> 02:09:12,183
It's not an errand!

1497
02:09:12,933 --> 02:09:13,983
It's a deal.

1498
02:09:15,519 --> 02:09:17,309
I need you to take care of someone for me.

1499
02:09:17,938 --> 02:09:20,018
I want your help.

1500
02:09:20,107 --> 02:09:22,737
If you couldn't handle him on your own,

1501
02:09:23,194 --> 02:09:25,034
he must be quite strong.

1502
02:09:25,112 --> 02:09:27,362
He holds a really deep grudge,

1503
02:09:27,740 --> 02:09:30,660
so one of my people could get hurt
if I'm not cautious.

1504
02:09:33,412 --> 02:09:36,172
Quietly bring him to me.

1505
02:09:37,208 --> 02:09:38,828
It's your request.

1506
02:09:39,752 --> 02:09:41,002
How can I reject it?

1507
02:09:44,048 --> 02:09:47,968
But you'll need to do me a favor as well.

1508
02:09:59,605 --> 02:10:00,815
Go on.

1509
02:10:01,148 --> 02:10:03,188
There's someone
who's been causing me trouble.

1510
02:10:03,275 --> 02:10:06,565
It's an unsolved case
that has disgraced me.

1511
02:10:07,571 --> 02:10:09,951
If you bring that person
to Hotel del Luna,

1512
02:10:10,324 --> 02:10:11,954
I'll bring that vengeful ghost...

1513
02:10:13,828 --> 02:10:15,038
to you.

1514
02:10:16,997 --> 02:10:17,997
Deal.

1515
02:10:21,377 --> 02:10:24,257
Is Seol Ji-won that dangerous?

1516
02:10:24,338 --> 02:10:28,428
The reason your ill-fated relationship
is haunting you

1517
02:10:29,218 --> 02:10:30,548
may be me.

1518
02:10:31,846 --> 02:10:33,216
Mago told me that.

1519
02:10:33,556 --> 02:10:36,636
You made the flowers bloom,
so you will have to pay the price for it.

1520
02:10:37,226 --> 02:10:39,436
The price I have to pay
for making the flowers bloom

1521
02:10:40,396 --> 02:10:41,976
is having a vengeful ghost haunt me?

1522
02:10:42,064 --> 02:10:44,734
I don't want you to pay the price,

1523
02:10:44,817 --> 02:10:48,607
so I'll do everything I can
to clean up after you.

1524
02:10:50,823 --> 02:10:52,413
Thank you for that.

1525
02:10:54,201 --> 02:10:55,201
EMERGENCY FUND

1526
02:10:55,286 --> 02:10:56,536
Mr. Koo Chan-sung?

1527
02:10:56,620 --> 02:10:57,450
Here.

1528
02:10:57,621 --> 02:10:58,751
Please come in.

1529
02:10:59,540 --> 02:11:02,960
Is my job to see
how good of a doctor he is?

1530
02:11:04,879 --> 02:11:07,629
Take this with you.
Tell him this is why you came.

1531
02:11:16,181 --> 02:11:19,691
The hepatization slowed down
your stomach contractions,

1532
02:11:19,768 --> 02:11:23,518
which is why you have indigestion
and a pressure on your chest.

1533
02:11:23,606 --> 02:11:25,226
It must be due to stress.

1534
02:11:25,816 --> 02:11:29,446
Yes. I do have a lot on my mind lately.

1535
02:11:29,528 --> 02:11:30,778
Is that so?

1536
02:11:30,863 --> 02:11:33,573
You can get the acupuncture treatment
and some medicine.

1537
02:11:33,657 --> 02:11:37,537
It's best if you take
my herbal medicine too.

1538
02:11:37,620 --> 02:11:40,500
I don't need acupuncture or medicine.

1539
02:11:41,373 --> 02:11:43,963
The reason for my stress is money.

1540
02:11:44,960 --> 02:11:46,000
That's why

1541
02:11:46,587 --> 02:11:48,837
I came here after seeing this.
I need the money.

1542
02:11:48,923 --> 02:11:50,223
EMERGENCY FUND

1543
02:11:57,264 --> 02:11:59,524
This is your number, right?

1544
02:11:59,600 --> 02:12:02,900
We were running short on time.
What a relief.

1545
02:12:04,563 --> 02:12:06,363
I need to check something.

1546
02:12:13,614 --> 02:12:15,914
Your palm lines look good.

1547
02:12:16,784 --> 02:12:18,544
You have a good lifeline, too.

1548
02:12:23,374 --> 02:12:25,794
Give me one centimeter of your lifeline.

1549
02:12:25,876 --> 02:12:27,416
If you sell me your lifeline,

1550
02:12:28,921 --> 02:12:30,841
I will give you 50 million won.

1551
02:12:36,845 --> 02:12:38,885
He buys other people's lifelines

1552
02:12:38,973 --> 02:12:41,393
and keeps a person
who should be dead alive?

1553
02:12:41,642 --> 02:12:44,142
I guess that doctor really is great.

1554
02:12:44,937 --> 02:12:47,687
Is it possible to buy
other people's lifelines with money?

1555
02:12:47,773 --> 02:12:49,943
Well, if it is a fair deal.

1556
02:12:50,025 --> 02:12:52,355
It's not a fraud. He pays well.

1557
02:12:52,987 --> 02:12:55,197
So that's why the Grim Reaper
couldn't do anything.

1558
02:12:58,659 --> 02:13:02,079
The person who sold it
wouldn't have thought it was for real.

1559
02:13:02,162 --> 02:13:04,872
They would've thought it was easy money.

1560
02:13:05,249 --> 02:13:07,079
Only the buyer is desperate.

1561
02:13:07,167 --> 02:13:10,127
I guess he uses it to make more money.

1562
02:13:10,796 --> 02:13:12,966
Do you think he sells it
to a wealthy person?

1563
02:13:14,591 --> 02:13:17,551
An important person, I suppose.

1564
02:13:18,053 --> 02:13:20,763
You'll be having surgery tonight,

1565
02:13:20,848 --> 02:13:22,678
so let's feed you some meat. Let's go.

1566
02:13:22,766 --> 02:13:24,726
You just want to have meat, don't you?

1567
02:13:25,644 --> 02:13:26,524
There's...

1568
02:13:26,603 --> 02:13:28,563
A restaurant Kim Jun-hyun visited
around here.

1569
02:13:29,898 --> 02:13:31,818
I know. Let's go.

1570
02:13:39,950 --> 02:13:42,080
I got someone to sell his lifeline.

1571
02:13:42,286 --> 02:13:45,156
I was very worried
since the one who promised me backed out.

1572
02:13:46,957 --> 02:13:47,997
What a relief.

1573
02:13:48,333 --> 02:13:50,293
That means you have to spend

1574
02:13:51,420 --> 02:13:53,130
all the money you've saved up so far.

1575
02:13:56,550 --> 02:13:57,930
Money isn't the problem.

1576
02:13:58,010 --> 02:14:00,600
As long as I can save him,
that's all right.

1577
02:14:01,305 --> 02:14:03,015
But you worked so hard to earn that money.

1578
02:14:04,391 --> 02:14:06,141
The surgery is today.

1579
02:14:07,394 --> 02:14:08,774
I must take a look.

1580
02:14:19,073 --> 02:14:20,783
Hyeon-jin is sleeping.

1581
02:14:43,263 --> 02:14:45,183
You can get surgery today.

1582
02:14:52,022 --> 02:14:53,112
It's a boy?

1583
02:14:54,149 --> 02:14:55,189
Yes.

1584
02:14:55,442 --> 02:14:57,442
The life we must take away

1585
02:14:58,195 --> 02:14:59,565
is the couple's son.

1586
02:15:05,828 --> 02:15:09,368
I didn't know
Man-wol could look so stunning.

1587
02:15:10,624 --> 02:15:11,794
Once the flowers fall,

1588
02:15:11,875 --> 02:15:14,495
will that be the end of the Moon Tree?

1589
02:15:15,170 --> 02:15:16,260
Yes.

1590
02:15:16,755 --> 02:15:19,295
That means the death of Man-wol...

1591
02:15:21,969 --> 02:15:23,969
who I have chained to this tree.

1592
02:15:24,304 --> 02:15:28,604
Man-wol will finally
be able to go to the afterlife.

1593
02:15:28,892 --> 02:15:30,772
It's been too long

1594
02:15:32,354 --> 02:15:34,574
for Man-wol
who has blossomed to the fullest

1595
02:15:36,275 --> 02:15:40,395
and for the guy who had to remain

1596
02:15:42,030 --> 02:15:43,280
as a small light.

1597
02:15:56,211 --> 02:15:59,341
He turned back when I was
accompanying him to the afterlife.

1598
02:16:01,717 --> 02:16:04,047
He's managed to stay here
for such a long time.

1599
02:16:28,660 --> 02:16:30,080
You should

1600
02:16:31,497 --> 02:16:32,997
get going too.

1601
02:17:28,512 --> 02:17:30,182
Live your life as a traitor.

1602
02:17:30,931 --> 02:17:32,811
That way, Man-wol can live.

1603
02:18:00,502 --> 02:18:03,092
I let him be
because you told me not to take him.

1604
02:18:03,380 --> 02:18:05,340
It is quite impressive

1605
02:18:05,424 --> 02:18:09,304
that a soul of a human can remain
for this long as a small light.

1606
02:18:09,886 --> 02:18:12,306
It's a curse he cast upon himself.

1607
02:18:13,098 --> 02:18:14,558
He's

1608
02:18:15,809 --> 02:18:18,729
staying here as a small light
because of the promise

1609
02:18:19,813 --> 02:18:21,773
he made to Man-wol.

1610
02:18:22,357 --> 02:18:23,777
Ms. Jang

1611
02:18:24,276 --> 02:18:26,816
took an assignment from me
in order to lessen the burden

1612
02:18:26,903 --> 02:18:29,033
on Koo Chan-sung
for making her flowers blossom.

1613
02:18:31,199 --> 02:18:33,989
It sounds like Man-wol doesn't know

1614
02:18:34,870 --> 02:18:38,620
the price Chan-sung has to pay yet.

1615
02:18:40,459 --> 02:18:41,959
Once she finds out,

1616
02:18:42,836 --> 02:18:44,916
she will be sad

1617
02:18:45,964 --> 02:18:48,264
and scared.

1618
02:19:16,787 --> 02:19:20,037
Are you nervous
that he might take your lifeline?

1619
02:19:21,875 --> 02:19:23,745
I guess you must want to live a long life.

1620
02:19:24,002 --> 02:19:26,302
Don't worry. You'll live a long life.

1621
02:19:27,339 --> 02:19:29,129
I was trying to figure it out.

1622
02:19:31,843 --> 02:19:34,353
How his parents must have felt
to buy someone else's lifelines

1623
02:19:35,639 --> 02:19:36,889
and attach them on their son.

1624
02:19:54,032 --> 02:19:56,372
That means I'll protect you,
so he can't take away yours.

1625
02:19:58,078 --> 02:20:00,208
I'm just protecting your lifeline.

1626
02:20:04,793 --> 02:20:06,843
They just don't want
to let go of their son.

1627
02:20:08,880 --> 02:20:11,340
They must be desperate to hold onto him.

1628
02:20:24,730 --> 02:20:26,310
You're here already.

1629
02:20:27,774 --> 02:20:29,484
Let's go to the treatment room.

1630
02:20:36,992 --> 02:20:39,292
It will neither hurt nor harm you.

1631
02:20:39,369 --> 02:20:41,079
I'll cut off exactly one centimeter.

1632
02:20:47,753 --> 02:20:49,173
Are you cutting my lifeline

1633
02:20:50,589 --> 02:20:52,219
to give it to your child?

1634
02:20:57,053 --> 02:21:01,063
Earlier today,
I heard that you have a sick son.

1635
02:21:09,566 --> 02:21:11,436
My son was severely ill.

1636
02:21:13,695 --> 02:21:16,445
After hearing about the lifeline surgery
overseas,

1637
02:21:16,740 --> 02:21:19,450
I tried it out
because I had nothing to lose.

1638
02:21:21,536 --> 02:21:25,116
Like a miracle, my son lived.

1639
02:21:26,708 --> 02:21:28,538
Both of you are still young.

1640
02:21:30,212 --> 02:21:32,052
It must've been quite an ordeal for you.

1641
02:21:33,548 --> 02:21:34,968
My son is young,

1642
02:21:35,717 --> 02:21:37,757
but my wife and I look quite old.

1643
02:21:39,971 --> 02:21:41,181
People think

1644
02:21:43,266 --> 02:21:45,596
we are his grandparents.

1645
02:22:44,953 --> 02:22:46,083
Hello?

1646
02:22:46,162 --> 02:22:48,372
DEMIAN

1647
02:22:50,166 --> 02:22:51,586
Were you reading a book?

1648
02:22:53,336 --> 02:22:55,006
That's a hard book.

1649
02:22:56,089 --> 02:22:57,839
It's not that hard.

1650
02:22:57,924 --> 02:23:01,854
I think it's all right
to show off how intelligent you are

1651
02:23:01,928 --> 02:23:03,348
if you're really that smart.

1652
02:23:03,972 --> 02:23:05,272
I like you.

1653
02:23:05,515 --> 02:23:08,435
Ma'am, are you the Grim Reaper too?

1654
02:23:10,103 --> 02:23:11,943
On the days I had surgery,

1655
02:23:12,022 --> 02:23:15,482
I always saw a man dressed
in a black suit in my dream.

1656
02:23:18,403 --> 02:23:22,323
He and I have totally different
themes for our black outfits.

1657
02:23:22,574 --> 02:23:24,284
He's just wearing black clothes.

1658
02:23:24,367 --> 02:23:27,997
And I'm wearing midnight black
with a hint of dark blue.

1659
02:23:29,247 --> 02:23:32,457
Midnight black and black are the same.

1660
02:23:33,043 --> 02:23:34,043
Really?

1661
02:23:34,836 --> 02:23:35,916
Whatever.

1662
02:23:36,630 --> 02:23:39,090
I am here to do something similar
to what he does.

1663
02:23:40,926 --> 02:23:43,926
I can't take you against your will.

1664
02:23:44,638 --> 02:23:47,468
You're a smart boy,
so you can hear me out,

1665
02:23:47,557 --> 02:23:49,347
think about it, and make a decision.

1666
02:23:54,481 --> 02:23:55,901
You do know

1667
02:23:56,524 --> 02:23:59,444
that your mom and dad
suddenly aged a lot, don't you?

1668
02:24:08,495 --> 02:24:10,365
Is it because of this?

1669
02:24:14,334 --> 02:24:15,344
Yes.

1670
02:24:16,920 --> 02:24:18,710
What they've attached there is

1671
02:24:20,131 --> 02:24:22,181
the lives of your mom and dad.

1672
02:24:23,677 --> 02:24:25,507
You paid the price,

1673
02:24:26,262 --> 02:24:29,272
so your desperation
to save your child was heard.

1674
02:24:29,849 --> 02:24:31,639
You didn't buy someone else's life.

1675
02:24:32,644 --> 02:24:34,814
You gave parts of your lives
to your child.

1676
02:24:34,896 --> 02:24:36,896
That's why you two
have aged a lot quicker.

1677
02:24:38,817 --> 02:24:42,067
I am not sure what you know,

1678
02:24:42,153 --> 02:24:45,493
but if my son lives,
I don't care what it takes.

1679
02:24:45,573 --> 02:24:49,163
Sadly, the child will
have to make the decision.

1680
02:24:50,954 --> 02:24:52,584
Once he makes the decision,

1681
02:24:54,916 --> 02:24:56,376
you must let him go.

1682
02:25:23,903 --> 02:25:26,163
Hyeon-jin!

1683
02:25:29,117 --> 02:25:31,577
-Wake up.
-Hyeon-jin.

1684
02:25:31,661 --> 02:25:34,211
What's wrong with him, honey?

1685
02:25:34,289 --> 02:25:35,499
Hyeon-jin.

1686
02:25:35,582 --> 02:25:37,582
Honey, what's wrong with him?

1687
02:25:37,667 --> 02:25:41,087
No, not yet, honey. What's wrong with him?

1688
02:25:41,171 --> 02:25:42,171
Honey...

1689
02:25:42,630 --> 02:25:44,380
No. Hyeon-jin, no.

1690
02:25:44,466 --> 02:25:47,256
No, wake up. Hyeon-jin!

1691
02:26:46,444 --> 02:26:48,574
I'm glad you resolved this.

1692
02:26:49,447 --> 02:26:50,697
If you had been any later,

1693
02:26:51,074 --> 02:26:53,414
I would've had to take away
all three of them.

1694
02:26:54,410 --> 02:26:55,500
His parents

1695
02:26:56,746 --> 02:26:59,666
may have wanted that.

1696
02:27:02,085 --> 02:27:03,545
If I go with you,

1697
02:27:04,254 --> 02:27:07,764
it'll be more painful for my mom and dad.

1698
02:27:10,093 --> 02:27:12,143
That's not for you to worry about.

1699
02:27:13,054 --> 02:27:14,684
It's for those who are left behind.

1700
02:27:34,200 --> 02:27:35,410
But...

1701
02:27:36,870 --> 02:27:40,540
I'm really afraid of that.

1702
02:28:03,854 --> 02:28:05,404
I'm afraid...

1703
02:28:13,364 --> 02:28:14,874
Do not be afraid.

1704
02:28:15,324 --> 02:28:18,664
I will find the evil ghost
just as I promised.

1705
02:28:23,082 --> 02:28:24,082
Okay.

1706
02:28:24,875 --> 02:28:27,625
Find that in a hurry
so that no one won't be scared anymore.

1707
02:28:44,687 --> 02:28:46,607
Even if it means I must give everything,

1708
02:28:47,148 --> 02:28:49,438
I still cannot let go.

1709
02:28:59,118 --> 02:29:02,328
After I, it's N, E, S, S, not Y.

1710
02:29:02,413 --> 02:29:04,083
-Isn't this right?
-Come.

1711
02:29:14,467 --> 02:29:17,177
-You did that on purpose, right?
-Blowing on it helps?

1712
02:29:17,261 --> 02:29:19,391
What does that look like to you?

1713
02:29:19,472 --> 02:29:23,392
The intern and the receptionist are
dating at work.

1714
02:29:23,517 --> 02:29:25,057
My goodness.

1715
02:29:25,352 --> 02:29:28,192
She just started here.
I can't believe they're dating already.

1716
02:29:28,272 --> 02:29:30,072
They're young.

1717
02:29:30,191 --> 02:29:32,741
A man and a woman are bound
to hit it off when they're together.

1718
02:29:32,818 --> 02:29:35,488
I guess it doesn't matter
if it's this life or the afterlife.

1719
02:29:35,738 --> 02:29:36,858
Goodness.

1720
02:29:37,907 --> 02:29:42,077
We've been together for 200 years,
but we're still very professional.

1721
02:29:43,913 --> 02:29:46,173
It wouldn't happen even after 2,000 years.

1722
02:29:46,248 --> 02:29:48,288
You aren't my type.

1723
02:29:48,375 --> 02:29:50,085
Not even in your dreams.

1724
02:29:50,169 --> 02:29:52,509
My dream? I didn't dream anything.

1725
02:29:53,214 --> 02:29:54,424
Hey, listen.

1726
02:29:54,715 --> 02:29:56,465
I don't like you either.

1727
02:30:16,654 --> 02:30:17,864
You're back already?

1728
02:30:19,532 --> 02:30:20,572
Yes.

1729
02:30:35,047 --> 02:30:39,257
Did Sanchez go crazy
after he went to the funeral?

1730
02:30:39,552 --> 02:30:40,722
What's with him?

1731
02:30:45,766 --> 02:30:47,516
Actually, I need to tell you something.

1732
02:30:50,563 --> 02:30:52,063
How did the funeral go?

1733
02:30:52,815 --> 02:30:54,185
You should have stayed longer.

1734
02:30:54,525 --> 02:30:55,935
I couldn't.

1735
02:30:57,111 --> 02:30:59,661
Veronica is still at your hotel.

1736
02:31:03,492 --> 02:31:04,872
Am I right, Chan-sung?

1737
02:31:06,537 --> 02:31:08,037
She's still there, isn't she?

1738
02:31:10,541 --> 02:31:13,921
He sounded so desperate,
so I couldn't tell him no.

1739
02:31:14,879 --> 02:31:17,049
He knows that he cannot come to the hotel

1740
02:31:17,131 --> 02:31:19,221
or see her even if he comes there.

1741
02:31:21,427 --> 02:31:23,047
But he thinks she's still at our hotel

1742
02:31:24,054 --> 02:31:26,064
even though he cannot see her.

1743
02:31:27,516 --> 02:31:31,056
I'll have a talk with him,
so please just play along.

1744
02:31:31,145 --> 02:31:32,475
Just until he gets better.

1745
02:31:32,563 --> 02:31:34,443
When will he get better?

1746
02:31:49,580 --> 02:31:52,120
Man-wol, thank you
for what you did last time.

1747
02:31:54,668 --> 02:31:56,128
I said goodbye to her thanks to you.

1748
02:31:59,506 --> 02:32:02,046
I'm making something that Veronica liked.

1749
02:32:02,843 --> 02:32:05,393
She loved it whenever I cooked it for her.

1750
02:32:05,846 --> 02:32:08,016
Can you bring it to her?

1751
02:32:10,309 --> 02:32:12,059
Sure, let's do that.

1752
02:32:15,189 --> 02:32:16,149
Chan-sung.

1753
02:32:17,650 --> 02:32:20,320
You're really bad at acting.

1754
02:32:20,945 --> 02:32:22,695
If you're going to do it, do it right.

1755
02:32:26,784 --> 02:32:29,914
Sanchez, do you have anything else
other than pizza for her?

1756
02:32:30,287 --> 02:32:34,417
You know, the shoes or jewelry
that Veronica used to like.

1757
02:32:34,792 --> 02:32:36,212
Oh, I can take a car too.

1758
02:32:37,711 --> 02:32:39,421
Can you really take it to her?

1759
02:32:39,505 --> 02:32:42,625
Of course, bring everything.
I'll take anything to her.

1760
02:32:43,425 --> 02:32:45,545
Oh, we have a sea in my hotel.

1761
02:32:45,636 --> 02:32:46,716
How about the yacht?

1762
02:32:46,804 --> 02:32:50,274
It would be great
if she plays on that yacht at the hotel.

1763
02:32:50,516 --> 02:32:51,346
Jang Man-wol!

1764
02:32:51,433 --> 02:32:52,273
What?

1765
02:32:54,728 --> 02:32:56,648
I'm comforting him.

1766
02:32:58,232 --> 02:33:02,442
If Sanchez doesn't get better soon,
he'll end up giving me everything he has.

1767
02:33:20,004 --> 02:33:21,094
Why are you doing this?

1768
02:33:21,171 --> 02:33:23,971
It's because you didn't tell him
the truth.

1769
02:33:24,049 --> 02:33:26,049
I'm trying to comfort him
because he's in pain.

1770
02:33:26,260 --> 02:33:27,550
Do you find that silly?

1771
02:33:27,636 --> 02:33:29,886
Yes, it's ridiculous to me.

1772
02:33:30,681 --> 02:33:33,351
Parents who buy lifelines
for their almost dead son,

1773
02:33:33,434 --> 02:33:36,024
and your friend who's making pizza
for his dead girlfriend.

1774
02:33:37,438 --> 02:33:38,938
They all look ridiculous to me.

1775
02:33:44,028 --> 02:33:46,778
They look pathetic and make me angry.

1776
02:33:47,406 --> 02:33:49,316
Don't you dare turn
into someone like them.

1777
02:33:54,329 --> 02:33:56,459
Why do you assume
that I won't be just like them?

1778
02:33:58,917 --> 02:34:00,247
I don't want to let you go.

1779
02:34:01,503 --> 02:34:02,633
I don't want to send you off.

1780
02:34:02,713 --> 02:34:05,013
The thought of not being able to see you
drives me crazy.

1781
02:34:06,091 --> 02:34:07,221
How...

1782
02:34:10,262 --> 02:34:12,222
How could you tell me to be okay?

1783
02:34:20,439 --> 02:34:22,979
You're the one who must send me off.

1784
02:34:24,359 --> 02:34:25,899
Tell me that you'll be okay.

1785
02:34:36,955 --> 02:34:38,865
If you don't tell me you'll be okay,

1786
02:34:41,126 --> 02:34:42,286
I'll be...

1787
02:34:45,047 --> 02:34:46,547
too scared.

1788
02:34:56,767 --> 02:34:58,097
A long time ago,

1789
02:35:00,270 --> 02:35:02,650
I told you that I was afraid
of paying the price

1790
02:35:03,941 --> 02:35:06,571
if I did stay by your side
and look into you.

1791
02:35:11,782 --> 02:35:13,452
I guess this is the price.

1792
02:35:18,330 --> 02:35:20,290
Becoming a nuisance...

1793
02:35:22,751 --> 02:35:24,711
that you despise.

1794
02:35:32,803 --> 02:35:33,853
Go.

1795
02:35:35,472 --> 02:35:37,562
I'll go to my friend.

1796
02:36:45,000 --> 02:36:46,210
She's not there anymore.

1797
02:36:47,836 --> 02:36:49,546
Veronica isn't there, is she?

1798
02:37:41,223 --> 02:37:43,393
Your flowers will begin to fall

1799
02:37:43,934 --> 02:37:46,144
when you become afraid.

1800
02:38:28,770 --> 02:38:30,730
When I first met you,

1801
02:38:33,775 --> 02:38:36,985
the flowers around here
blossomed beautifully.

1802
02:38:42,409 --> 02:38:44,239
Now, all of them are gone.

1803
02:38:49,541 --> 02:38:50,631
That day,

1804
02:38:51,835 --> 02:38:55,165
you were utterly scared
after seeing a ghost.

1805
02:39:03,305 --> 02:39:04,885
Today, I'm the scared one.

1806
02:39:14,274 --> 02:39:15,534
The flowers...

1807
02:39:20,197 --> 02:39:21,697
are falling off the tree.

1808
02:39:35,587 --> 02:39:36,797
I see.

1809
02:39:41,218 --> 02:39:43,718
The petals don't even remain
in this world.

1810
02:39:48,016 --> 02:39:50,436
They vanish
even before touching the ground.

1811
02:39:58,819 --> 02:40:00,239
I guess...

1812
02:40:04,157 --> 02:40:05,827
nothing will remain.

1813
02:40:10,789 --> 02:40:12,119
Maybe,

1814
02:40:15,585 --> 02:40:17,955
the flowers falling off your tree...

1815
02:40:20,799 --> 02:40:23,219
are falling onto me.

1816
02:40:25,470 --> 02:40:27,810
Just like the first leaf did.

1817
02:40:35,564 --> 02:40:37,364
And those petals have piled up.

1818
02:40:40,193 --> 02:40:41,653
So it's gotten heavier...

1819
02:40:43,864 --> 02:40:45,284
and painful to carry.

1820
02:40:50,078 --> 02:40:52,578
I'll consider shouldering the pile
as solely my responsibility.

1821
02:41:00,255 --> 02:41:01,505
So...

1822
02:41:06,052 --> 02:41:08,352
Don't be afraid when you leave me behind.

1823
02:41:21,693 --> 02:41:22,903
This is...

1824
02:41:25,238 --> 02:41:27,318
how I, just a weak human,

1825
02:41:32,704 --> 02:41:34,924
love you...

1826
02:41:42,172 --> 02:41:43,672
with all my heart.

1827
02:42:06,696 --> 02:42:09,446
It's too heartbreaking
if I remain only as a flower petal

1828
02:42:11,868 --> 02:42:13,748
that's bound to vanish.

1829
02:44:48,733 --> 02:44:50,783
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
